description: lxml is a pythonic mature binding for the libxml and libxslt library it provides safe and convenient access to these library using the elementtree api it extends the elementtree api significantly to offer support for xpath relaxng xml schema xslt c n and much more to contact the project go to the project home page or see our bug tracker at http launchpad net lxmlin case you want to use the current in development version of lxml you can get it from the github repository at http github com lxml lxml note that this requires cython to build the source see the build instruction on the project home page to the same end running easy install lxml dev will install lxml from http github com lxml lxml tarball master egg lxml dev if you have an appropriate version of cython installed after an official release of a new stable series bug fix may become available at http github com lxml lxml tree lxml running easy install lxml bugfix will install the unreleased branch state from http github com lxml lxml tarball lxml egg lxml bugfix a soon a a maintenance branch ha been established note that this requires cython to be installed at an appropriate version for the build bug fixeda crash wa resolved when using iterwalk or canonicalize after parsing certain incorrect input note that iterwalk can crash on valid input parsed with the same parser after failing to parse the incorrect input

description: make ansi escape character sequence for producing colored terminal text and cursor positioning work under m window pypi for release github for source colorama for enterprise on tideliftif you find colorama useful please to the author thank you tested on cpython and and pypy and no requirement other than the standard library ansi escape character sequence have long been used to produce colored terminal text and cursor positioning on unix and mac colorama make this work on window too by wrapping stdout stripping ansi sequence it find which would appear a gobbledygook in the output and converting them into the appropriate win call to modify the state of the terminal on other platform colorama doe nothing this ha the upshot of providing a simple cross platform api for printing colored terminal text from python and ha the happy side effect that existing application or library which use ansi sequence to produce colored output on linux or mac can now also work on window simply by calling colorama just fix window console since v or colorama init all version but may have other side effect see below an alternative approach is to install ansi sys on window machine which provides the same behaviour for all application running in terminal colorama is intended for situation where that isn t easy e g maybe your app doesn t have an installer demo script in the source code repository print some colored text using ansi sequence compare their output under gnome terminal s built in ansi handling versus on window command prompt using colorama these screenshots show that on window colorama doe not support ansi dim text it look the same a normal text if the only thing you want from colorama is to get ansi escape to work on window then run if you re on a recent version of window or better and your stdout stderr are pointing to a window console then this will flip the magic configuration switch to enable window built in ansi support if you re on an older version of window and your stdout stderr are pointing to a window console then this will wrap sys stdout and or sys stderr in a magic file object that intercept ansi escape sequence and issue the appropriate win call to emulate them in all other circumstance it doe nothing whatsoever basically the idea is that this make window act like unix with respect to ansi escape handling it s safe to call this function multiple time it s safe to call this function on non window platform but it won t do anything it s safe to call this function when one or both of your stdout stderr are redirected to a file it won t do anything to those stream alternatively you can use the older interface with more feature but also more potential footguns this doe the same thing a just fix window console except for the following difference it s not safe to call init multiple time you can end up with multiple layer of wrapping and broken ansi support colorama will apply a heuristic to guess whether stdout stderr support ansi and if it think they don t then it will wrap sys stdout and sys stderr in a magic file object that strip out ansi escape sequence before printing them this happens on all platform and can be convenient if you want to write your code to emit ansi escape sequence unconditionally and let colorama decide whether they should actually be output but note that colorama s heuristic is not particularly clever init also accepts explicit keyword args to enable disable various functionality see below to stop using colorama before your program exit simply call deinit this will restore stdout and stderr to their original value so that colorama is disabled to resume using colorama again call reinit it is cheaper than calling init again but doe the same thing most user should depend on colorama and use just fix window console the old init interface will be supported indefinitely for backwards compatibility but we don t plan to fix any issue with it also for backwards compatibility cross platform printing of colored text can then be done using colorama s constant shorthand for ansi escape sequence these are deliberately rudimentary see below or simply by manually printing ansi sequence from your own code or colorama can be used in conjunction with existing ansi library such a the venerable termcolor the fabulous blessing or the incredible rich if you wish colorama s fore back and style constant were more capable then consider using one of the above highly capable library to generate color etc and use colorama just for it primary purpose to convert those ansi sequence to also work on window similarly do not send pr adding the generation of new ansi type to colorama we are only interested in converting ansi code to win api call not shortcut like the above to generate ansi character available formatting constant are style reset all reset foreground background and brightness colorama will perform this reset automatically on program exit these are fairly well supported but not part of the standard ansi code to reposition the cursor are supported see demo demo py for an example of how to generate them init accepts some kwargs to override default behaviour if you find yourself repeatedly sending reset sequence to turn off color change at the end of every print then init autoreset true will automate that pas true or false to override whether ansi code should be stripped from the output the default behaviour is to strip if on window or if output is redirected not a tty pas true or false to override whether to convert ansi code in the output into win call the default behaviour is to convert if on window and output is to a tty terminal on window colorama work by replacing sys stdout and sys stderr with proxy object which override the write method to do their work if this wrapping cause you problem then this can be disabled by passing init wrap false the default behaviour is to wrap if autoreset or strip or convert are true when wrapping is disabled colored printing on non window platform will continue to work a normal to do cross platform colored output you can use colorama s ansitowin proxy directly ansi sequence generally take the form where param is an integer and command is a single letter zero or more params are passed to a command if no params are passed it is generally synonymous with passing a single zero no space exist in the sequence they have been inserted here simply to read more easily the only ansi sequence that colorama convert into win call are multiple numeric params to the m command can be combined into a single sequence all other ansi sequence of the form esc param param command are silently stripped from the output on window any other form of ansi sequence such a single character code or alternative initial character are not recognised or stripped it would be cool to add them though let me know if it would be useful for you via the issue on github i ve personally only tested it on window xp cmd console ubuntu gnome terminal xterm and o x some valid ansi sequence aren t recognised if you re hacking on the code see readme hacking md especially see the explanation there of why we do not want pr that allow colorama to generate new type of ansi code see outstanding issue and wish list http github com tartley colorama issuesif anything doesn t work for you or doesn t do what you expected or hoped for i d love to hear about it on that issue list would be delighted by patch and would be happy to grant commit access to anyone who submits a working patch or two copyright jonathan hartley arnon yaari bsd clause license see license file professional support for colorama is available a part of the tidelift subscription tidelift give software development team a single source for purchasing and maintaining their software with professional grade assurance from the expert who know it best while seamlessly integrating with existing tool see the changelog for more thanks marc schlaich schlamar for a setup py fix for python marc abramowitz reported fixed a crash on exit with closed stdout providing a solution to issue s setuptools distutils debate and other fix user eryksun for guidance on correctly instantiating ctypes windll matthew mccormick for politely pointing out a longstanding crash on non win ben hoyt for a magnificent fix under bit window jesse at empty square for submitting a fix for example in the readme user jamessp an observant documentation fix for cursor positioning user vaal dave mckee lackner kristof for a tiny but much needed win fix julien stuyck for wisely suggesting python compatible update to readme daniel griffith for multiple fabulous patch oscar lesta for a valuable fix to stop ansi char being sent to non tty output roger binns for many suggestion valuable feedback bug report tim golden for thought and much appreciated feedback on the initial idea user zearin for update to the readme file john szakmeister for adding support for light colorscharles merriam for adding documentation to demosjurko for a fix on bit window cpython w o ctypesflorian bruhin for a fix when stdout or stderr are nonethomas weininger for fixing valueerror on windowsremi rampin for better github integration and fix to the readme filesimeon visser for closing a file handle using with and updating classifier to include python and andy neff for fixing reset of light ex color jonathan hartley for the initial idea and implementation

source saythen to install librosa sayif all went well you should be able to execute the following command from a python console this should print out a description of your software environment along with the installed version of other package used by librosa o x user should follow the installation guide given below alternatively you can download or clone the repository and use pip to handle dependency orby calling pip list you should see librosa now a an installed package back to top librosa us soundfile and audioread to load audio file note that soundfile doe not currently support mp which will cause librosa to fall back on the audioread library if you re using conda to install librosa then most audio coding dependency except mp will be handled automatically if you re using pip on description: loguru is a library which aim to bring enjoyable logging in python did you ever feel lazy about configuring a logger and used print instead i did yet logging is fundamental to every application and eas the process of debugging using loguru you have no excuse not to use logging from the start this is a simple a from loguru import logger also this library is intended to make python logging le painful by adding a bunch of useful functionality that solve caveat of the standard logger using log in your application should be an automatism loguru try to make it both pleasant and powerful ready to use out of the box without boilerplateno handler no formatter no filter one function to rule them alleasier file logging with rotation retention compressionmodern string formatting using brace styleexceptions catching within thread or mainpretty logging with colorsasynchronous thread safe multiprocess safefully descriptive exceptionsstructured logging a neededlazy evaluation of expensive functionscustomizable levelsbetter datetime handlingsuitable for script and librariesentirely compatible with standard loggingpersonalizable default through environment variablesconvenient parserexhaustive notifier x faster than built in loggingthe main concept of loguru is that there is one and only one logger for convenience it is pre configured and output to stderr to begin with but that s entirely configurable the logger is just an interface which dispatch log message to configured handler simple right how to add a handler how to set up log formatting how to filter message how to set level one answer the add function this function should be used to register sink which are responsible for managing log message contextualized with a record dict a sink can take many form a simple function a string path a file like object a coroutine function or a built in handler note that you may also remove a previously added handler by using the identifier returned while adding it this is particularly useful if you want to supersede the default stderr handler just call logger remove to make a fresh start if you want to send logged message to a file you just have to use a string path a the sink it can be automatically timed too for convenience it is also easily configurable if you need rotating logger if you want to remove older log or if you wish to compress your file at closure loguru favor the much more elegant and powerful formatting over logging function are actually equivalent to str format have you ever seen your program crashing unexpectedly without seeing anything in the log file did you ever notice that exception occurring in thread were not logged this can be solved using the catch decorator context manager which ensures that any error is correctly propagated to the logger loguru automatically add color to your log if your terminal is compatible you can define your favorite style by using markup tag in the sink format all sink added to the logger are thread safe by default they are not multiprocess safe but you can enqueue the message to ensure log integrity this same argument can also be used if you want async logging coroutine function used a sink are also supported and should be awaited with complete logging exception that occur in your code is important to track bug but it s quite useless if you don t know why it failed loguru help you identify problem by allowing the entire stack trace to be displayed including value of variable thanks better exception for this the code would result in want your log to be serialized for easier parsing or to pas them around using the serialize argument each log message will be converted to a json string before being sent to the configured sink using bind you can contextualize your logger message by modifying the extra record attribute it is possible to modify a context local state temporarily with contextualize you can also have more fine grained control over your log by combining bind and filter finally the patch method allows dynamic value to be attached to the record dict of each new message sometime you would like to log verbose information without performance penalty in production you can use the opt method to achieve this loguru come with all standard logging level to which trace and success are added do you need more then just create it by using the level function the standard logging is bloated with argument like datefmt or msec asctime s and created s naive datetimes without timezone information not intuitive formatting etc loguru fix it using the logger in your script is easy and you can configure it at start to use loguru from inside a library remember to never call add but use disable instead so logging function become no op if a developer wish to see your library s log he can enable it again wish to use built in logging handler a a loguru sink need to propagate loguru message to standard logging want to intercept standard logging message toward your loguru sink don t like the default logger formatting would prefer another debug color no problem it is often useful to extract specific information from generated log this is why loguru provides a parse method which help to deal with log and regexes loguru can easily be combined with the great notifiers library must be installed separately to receive an e mail when your program fail unexpectedly or to send many other kind of notification although logging impact on performance is in most case negligible a zero cost logger would allow to use it anywhere without much concern in an upcoming release loguru s critical function will be implemented in c for maximum speed api referencehelp guidestype hintscontributinglicensechangelog

description: manipulation and analysis of geometric object in the cartesian plane shapely is a bsd licensed python package for manipulation and analysis of planar geometric object it is based on the widely deployed geos the engine of postgis and jts from which geos is ported library shapely is not concerned with data format or coordinate system but can be readily integrated with package that are for more detail see shapely github repositoryshapely documentation and manualhere is the canonical example of building an approximately circular patch by buffering a point see the manual for more example and guidance shapely requirespython geos shapely may be installed from a source distribution or one of several kind of built distribution built distribution are the only option for user who do not have or do not know how to use their platform s compiler and python sdk and a good option for user who would rather not bother linux o x and window user can get shapely wheel with geos included from the python package index with a recent version of pip shapely is available via system package management tool like apt yum and homebrew and is also provided by popular python distribution like canopy and anaconda if you use the conda package manager to install shapely be sure to use the conda forge channel window user have another good installation option the wheel published at http www lfd uci edu gohlke pythonlibs shapely these can be installed using pip by specifying the entire url if you want to build shapely from source for compatibility with other module that depend on geos such a cartopy or osgeo ogr or want to use a different version of geos than the one included in the project wheel you should first install the geos library cython and numpy on your system using apt yum brew or other mean and then direct pip to ignore the binary wheel if you ve installed geos to a standard location the geos config program will be used to get compiler and linker option if geos config is not on your executable it can be specified with a geos config environment variable e g shapely doe not read or write data file but it can serialize and deserialize using several well known format and protocol the shapely wkb and shapely wkt module provide dumper and loader inspired by python s pickle module shapely can also integrate with other python gi package using geojson like dicts dependency for developing shapely are listed in requirement dev txt cython and numpy are not required for production installation only for development use of a virtual environment is strongly recommended the project us pytest to run shapely s suite of unittests and doctests question about using shapely may be asked on the gi stackexchange using the shapely tag bug may be reported at http github com description: pathos is a framework for heterogeneous computing it provides a consistent high level interface for configuring and launching parallel computation across heterogeneous resource pathos provides configurable launcher for parallel and distributed computing where each launcher contains the syntactic logic to configure and launch job in an execution environment example of launcher that plug into pathos are a queue le mpi based launcher in pyina a ssh based launcher in pathos and a multi process launcher in multiprocess pathos provides a consistent interface for parallel and or distributed version of map and apply for each launcher thus lowering the barrier for user to extend their code to parallel and or distributed resource the guiding design principle behind pathos is that map and apply should be drop in replacement in otherwise serial code and thus switching to one or more of the pathos launcher is all that is needed to enable code to leverage the selected parallel or distributed computing resource this not only greatly reduces the time to convert a code to parallel but it also enables a single code base to be maintained instead of requiring parallel serial and distributed version of a code pathos map can be nested thus hierarchical heterogeneous computing is possible by merely selecting the desired hierarchy of map and pipe apply object the pathos framework is composed of several interoperating package dill a utility to serialize all of pythonpox utility for filesystem exploration and automated buildsklepto persistent caching to memory disk or databasemultiprocess better multiprocessing and multithreading in pythonppft distributed and parallel pythonpyina mpi parallel map and cluster schedulingpathos graph management and execution in heterogeneous computingthe pathos package provides a few basic tool to make parallel and distributed computing more accessible to the end user the goal of pathos is to enable the user to extend their own code to parallel and distributed computing with minimal refactoring pathos provides method for configuring launching monitoring and controlling a service on a remote host one of the most basic feature of pathos is the ability to configure and launch a rpc based service on a remote host pathos seed the remote host with the portpicker script which allows the remote host to inform the localhost of a port that is available for communication beyond the ability to establish a rpc service and then post request is the ability to launch code in parallel unlike parallel computing performed at the node level typically with mpi pathos enables the user to launch job in parallel across heterogeneous distributed resource pathos provides distributed map and pipe algorithm where a mix of local processor and distributed worker can be selected pathos also provides a very basic automated load balancing service a well a the ability for the user to directly select the resource the high level pool map interface yield a map implementation that hide the rpc internals from the user with pool map the user can launch their code in parallel and a a distributed service using standard python and without writing a line of server or parallel batch code rpc server and communication in general is known to be insecure however instead of attempting to make the rpc communication itself secure pathos provides the ability to automatically wrap any distributes service or communication in a ssh tunnel ssh is a universally trusted method using ssh tunnel pathos ha launched several distributed calculation on national lab cluster and to date ha performed test calculation that utilize node to node communication between several national lab cluster and a user s laptop pathos allows the user to configure and launch at a very atomistic level through raw access to ssh and scp pathos is the core of a python framework for heterogeneous computing pathos is in active development so any user feedback bug report comment or suggestion are highly appreciated a list of issue is located at http github com uqfoundation pathos issue with a legacy list maintained at http uqfoundation github io project pathos query pathos provides a configurable distributed parallel map interface to launching rpc service call with a map interface that meet and extends the python map standardthe ability to submit service request to a selection of serversthe ability to tunnel server communication with sshthe pathos core is built on low level communication to remote host using ssh the interface to ssh scp and ssh tunneled connection can configure and launch remote process with sshconfigure and copy file object with scpestablish an tear down a ssh tunnelto get up and running quickly pathos also provides infrastructure to easily establish a ssh tunneled connection to a rpc serverthe latest released version of pathos is available from http pypi org project pathospathos is distributed under a clause bsd license you can get the latest development version with all the shiny new feature at http github com uqfoundationif you have a new contribution please submit a pull request pathos can be installed with pip pathos requires python or pypy setuptools pox dill ppft multiprocess probably the best way to get started is to look at the documentation at http pathos rtfd io also see pathos test and pathos example for a set of script that demonstrate the configuration and launching of communication with ssh and scp and demonstrate the configuration and execution of job in a hierarchical parallel workflow you can run the test suite with python m pathos test tunnel and other connection to remote server can be established with the pathos connect script or with python m pathos see pathos connect help for more information pathos also provides a portpicker script to select an open port also available with python m pathos portpicker the source code is generally well documented so further question may be resolved by inspecting the code itself please feel free to submit a ticket on github or ask a question on stackoverflow mike mckerns if you would like to share how you use pathos in your work please send an email to mmckerns at uqfoundation dot org important class and function are found here pathos abstract launcher the worker pool api definition pathos pool all of the pathos worker pool pathos core the high level command interface pathos host the hostname registry interface pathos serial serialpool the serial python worker pool pathos parallel parallelpool the parallelpython worker pool pathos multiprocessing processpool the multiprocessing worker pool pathos threading threadpool the multithreading worker pool pathos connection pipe the launcher base class pathos secure pipe the secure launcher base class pathos secure copier the secure copier base class pathos secure tunnel the secure tunnel base class pathos selector selector the selector base class pathos server server the server base class pathos profile profiling in thread and process pathos map standalone map instance pathos also provides two convenience script that are used to establish secure distributed connection these script are installed to a directory on the user s path and thus can be run from anywhere portpicker get the portnumber of an open port pathos connect establish tunnel and or rpc server typing help a an argument to any of the above script will print out an instructive help message if you use pathos to do research that lead to publication we ask that you acknowledge use of pathos by citing the following in your publication please see http uqfoundation github io project pathos or http arxiv org pdf for further information

description: a decorator override that verifies that a method that should override an inherited method actually doe it copy the docstring of the inherited method to the overridden method since signature validation and docstring inheritance are performed on class creation and not on class instantiation this library significantly improves the safety and experience of creating class hierarchy in python without significantly impacting performance see http stackoverflow com q for the initial inspiration for this library python ha no standard mechanism by which to guarantee that a method that previously overrode an inherited method continues to do so and a method that previously did not override an inherited will not override now this open the door for subtle problem a class hierarchy evolve over time for example a method that is added to a superclass is shadowed by an existing method with the same name in a subclass a method of a superclass that is overridden by a subclass is renamed in the superclass but not in the subclass a method of a superclass that is overridden by a subclass is removed in the superclass but not in the subclass a method of a superclass that is overridden by a subclass but the signature of the overridden method is incompatible with that of the inherited one these can be only checked by explicitly marking method override in the code python also ha no standard mechanism by which to inherit docstrings in overridden method because most standard linters e g flake have rule that require all public method to have a docstring this inevitably lead to a proliferation of see parent class for usage docstrings on overridden method or worse to a disabling of these rule altogether in addition mediocre or missing docstrings degrade the quality of tooltips and completion that can be provided by an editor compatible with python use override to indicate that a subclass method should override a superclass method use enforceoverrides to require subclass method that shadow superclass method to be decorated with override use final to indicate that a superclass method cannot be overriden with python and above final is directly typing final note that classmethod and staticmethod must be declared before override this project exists only through the work of all the people who contribute mkorpela drorasaf ngoodman tyleryep leeopop donpatrice jayvdb joelgrus lisyarus soulmerge rkr at dbx ashwin brentyi jobh tjsmart

can add them in one go with add row you can add data one column at a time a well to do this you use the add column method which take two argument a string which is the name for the field the column you are adding corresponds to and a list or tuple which contains the column data if you really want to you can even mix and match add row and add column and build some of your table in one way and some of it in the other table built this way are kind of confusing for other people to read though so don t do this unless you have a good reason if you have your table data in a comma separated value file csv you can read this data into a prettytable like this if you have your table data in a database which you can access using a library which confirms to the python db api e g an sqlite database mechanism for determining the credential to use by default smart open will defer to boto and let the latter take care of the credential there are several way to override this behavior the first is to pas a boto client object a a transport parameter to the open function you can customize the credential when constructing the session for the client smart open will then use the session when talking to description: optax is a gradient processing and optimization library for jax optax is designed to facilitate research by providing building block that can be easily recombined in custom way our goal are towe favour focusing on small composable building block that can be effectively combined into custom solution others may build upon these basic component more complicated abstraction whenever reasonable implementation prioritise readability and structuring code to match standard equation over code reuse an initial prototype of this library wa made available in jax s experimental folder a jax experimental optix given the wide adoption across deepmind of optix and after a few iteration on the api optix wa eventually moved out of experimental a a standalone open source library renamed optax documentation on optax can be found at optax readthedocs io optax can be installed with pip directly from github with the following command or from pypi optax contains implementation of many popular optimizers and loss function for example the following code snippet us the adam optimizer from optax adam and the mean squared error from optax l loss we initialize the optimizer state using the init function and params of the model to write the update loop we need a loss function that can be differentiated by jax with jax grad in this example to obtain the gradient the gradient are then converted via optimizer update to obtain the update that should be applied to the current params to obtain the new one optax apply update is a convinience utility to do this you can continue the quick start in the optax quickstart notebook we refer to the doc for a detailed list of available optax component here we highlight the main category of buiilding block provided by optax one of the key building block of optax is a gradienttransformation each transformation is defined two function the init function initializes a possibly empty set of statistic aka state and the update function transforms a candidate gradient given some statistic and optionally the current value of the parameter for example the fact that transformation take candidate gradient a input and return processed gradient a output in contrast to returning the updated parameter is critical to allow to combine arbitrary transformation into a custom optimiser gradient processor and also allows to combine transformation for different gradient that operate on a shared set of variable for instance chain combine them sequentially and return a new gradienttransformation that applies several transformation in sequence for example optax also provides several wrapper that take a gradienttransformation a input and return a new gradienttransformation that modifies the behaviour of the inner transformation in a specific way for instance the flatten wrapper flattens gradient into a single large vector before applying the inner gradienttransformation the transformed updated are then unflattened before being returned to the user this can be used to reduce the overhead of performing many calculation on lot of small variable at the cost of increasing memory usage for example other example of wrapper include accumulating gradient over multiple step or applying the inner transformation only to specific parameter or at specific step many popular transformation use time dependent component e g to anneal some hyper parameter e g the learning rate optax provides for this purpose schedule that can be used to decay scalar a a function of a step count for example you may use a polynomial schedule with power to decay a hyper parameter linearly over a number of step schedule are used by certain gradient transformation for instance in addition to the low level building block we also provide alias for popular optimisers built using these component e g rmsprop adam adamw etc these are all still instance of a gradienttransformation and can therefore be further combined with any of the individual building block for example after transforming an update using a gradienttransformation or any custom manipulation of the update you will typically apply the update to a set of parameter this can be done trivially using tree map for convenience we expose an apply update function to apply update to parameter the function just add the update and the parameter together i e tree map lambda p u p u params update note that separating gradient transformation from the parameter update is critical to support composing sequence of transformation e g chain a well a combine multiple update to the same parameter e g in multi task setting where different task need different set of gradient transformation optax provides a number of standard loss used in deep learning such a l loss softmax cross entropy cosine distance etc the loss accept batch a input however they perform no reduction across the batch dimension s this is trivial to do in jax for example computing the hessian or fisher information matrix for neural network is typically intractable due to the quadratic memory requirement solving for the diagonal of these matrix is often a better solution the library offer function description: websocket client is a websocket client for python it provides access to low level apis for websockets websocket client implement version hybi of the websocket protocol this client doe not currently support the permessage deflate extension from rfc this project s documentation can be found at http websocket client readthedocs io please see the contribution guidelinesyou can use either python setup py install or pip install websocket client to install this module is tested on python there are several optional dependency that can be installed to enable specific websocket client feature while not a strict dependency rel is useful when using run forever with automatic reconnect install rel with pip install rel footnote some shell such a zsh require you to escape the and character with a check out the documentation s faq for additional guideline http websocket client readthedocs io en latest faq htmlknown issue with this library include lack of websocket compression support rfc and minimal threading documentation support the send and validate utf method can sometimes be bottleneck you can disable utf validation in this library and receive a performance enhancement with the skip utf validation parameter if you want to get better performance install wsaccel while websocket client doe not depend on wsaccel it will be used if available wsaccel double the speed of utf validation and offer a very minor performance boost when masking the payload data a part of the send process numpy used to be a suggested performance enhancement alternative but issue found it didn t help many more example are found in the example documentation most real world websockets situation involve longer lived connection the websocketapp run forever loop will automatically try to reconnect to an open websocket connection when a network connection is lost if it is provided with a dispatcher parameter and provides a variety of event based connection control run forever doe not automatically reconnect if the server close the websocket customizing behavior when the server close the websocket should be handled in the on close callback this example us rel for the dispatcher to provide automatic reconnection this is if you want to communicate a short message and disconnect immediately when done for example if you want to confirm that a websocket server is running and responds properly to a specific request

description: faker is a python package that generates fake data for you whether you need to bootstrap your database create good looking xml document fill in your persistence to stress test it or anonymize data taken from a production service faker is for you faker is heavily inspired by php faker perl faker and by ruby faker starting from version faker dropped support for python and from version only support python and above if you still need python compatibility please install version in the meantime and please consider updating your codebase to support python so you can enjoy the latest feature faker ha to offer please see the extended doc for more detail especially if you are upgrading from version and below a there might be breaking change this package wa also previously called fake factory which wa already deprecated by the end of and much ha changed since then so please ensure that your project and it dependency do not depend on the old package install with pip use faker faker to create and initialize a faker generator which can generate data by accessing property named after the type of data you want each call to method fake name yield a different random result this is because faker forward faker generator method name call to faker generator format method name faker also ha it own pytest plugin which provides a faker fixture you can use in your test please check out the pytest fixture doc to learn more each of the generator property like name address and lorem are called fake a faker generator ha many of them packaged in provider check the extended doc for a list of bundled provider and a list of community provider faker faker can take a locale a an argument to return localized data if no localized provider is found the factory fall back to the default lcid string for u english ie en u faker faker also support multiple locale new in v you can check available faker locale in the source code under the provider package the localization of faker is an ongoing process for which we need your help please don t hesitate to create a localized provider for your own locale and submit a pull request pr the faker constructor take a performance related argument called use weighting it specifies whether to attempt to have the frequency of value match real world frequency e g the english name gary would be much more frequent than the name lorimer if use weighting is false then all item have an equal chance of being selected and the selection process is much faster the default is true when installed you can invoke faker from the command line where faker is the script when installed in your environment in development you could use python m faker instead h help show a help message version show the program s version number o filename redirects the output to the specified filename l bg bg c cz zh cn zh tw allows use of a localized provider r repeat will generate a specified number of output s sep will generate the specified separator after each generated output i my custom provider other custom provider list of additional custom provider to use note that is the import path of the package containing your provider class not the custom provider class itself fake is the name of the fake to generate an output for such a name address or text fake argument optional argument to pas to the fake e g the profile fake take an optional list of comma separated field name a the first argument example dynamic provider can read element from an external source you can provide your own set of word if you don t want to use the default lorem ipsum one the following example show how to do it with a list of word picked from cakeipsum factory boy already ship with integration with faker simply use the factory faker method of factory boy the random property on the generator return the instance of random random used to generate the value by default all generator share the same instance of random random which can be accessed with from faker generator import random using this may be useful for plugins that want to affect all faker instance through use of the unique property on the generator you can guarantee that any generated value are unique for this specific instance calling fake unique clear clear the already seen value note to avoid infinite loop after a number of attempt to find a unique value faker will throw a uniquenessexception beware of the birthday paradox collision are more likely than you d think in addition only hashable argument and return value can be used with unique when using faker for unit testing you will often want to generate the same data set for convenience the generator also provide a seed method which seed the shared random number generator calling the same method with the same version of faker and seed produce the same result each generator can also be switched to it own instance of random random separate to the shared one by using the seed instance method which act the same way for example please note that a we keep updating datasets result are not guaranteed to be consistent across patch version if you hardcode result in your test make sure you pinned the version of faker down to the patch number if you are using pytest you can seed the faker fixture by defining a faker seed fixture please check out the pytest fixture doc to learn more run test write documentation for provider please see contributing faker is released under the mit license see the bundled license file for detail fzaninotto php fakerdistributebuildoutmodern package template

description: a crucial element of system for data analysis is laying out all the hyperparameters of that system so they can be easily examined and modified we add a few useful extension to a popular human readable data serialization language known a yaml yaml ain t markup language this provides support for a rather expansive idea of what constitutes a hyperparameter and clean up python file for data analysis to just the bare algorithm yaml is a data serialization language similar to json and it support three basic type of node scalar sequential and mapping pyyaml naturally convert sequential node to python list and mapping node to python dicts scalar node can take one of the following form note that we ve used a simple mapping to demonstrate the scalar node a mapping is a set of key value pair defined so that the key can be used to easily retrieve the corresponding value in addition to the format above mapping can also be specified in a similar manner to json sequence or list of item can also be specified in two way ornote that when not using the inline version yaml us whitespace to denote nested item yaml ha a few more advanced feature such a alias and merge key that you may want to explore on your own we will briefly discus one here since it is relevant for our extension yaml tag tag are added with a prefix and they specify the type of the node this allows type beyond the simple type listed above to be used pyyaml support a few additional type such a these can all be quite useful however we found that this system wa a bit cumbersome especially with the frequency with which we were using them so we decided to implement some shortcut for these feature which we are calling hyperpyyaml we make several extension to yaml including easier object creation nicer alias and tuples our first extension is to simplify the structure for specifying an instance module class or function a an example this tag prefixed with new construct an instance of the specified class if the node is a mapping node all the item are passed a keyword argument to the class when the instance is created a list can similarly be used to pas positional argument see the following example we also description: connexion is a framework that automagically handle http request based on openapi specification formerly known a swagger spec of your api described in yaml format connexion allows you to write an openapi specification then map the endpoint to your python function this make it unique a many tool generate the specification based on your python code you can describe your rest api in a much detail a you want then connexion guarantee that it will work a you specified we built connexion this way in order to simplify the development processconfirm expectation about what your api will look likevalidates request and endpoint parameter automatically based on your specificationprovides a web swagger console ui so that the user of your api can have live documentation and even call your api s endpoint through ithandles oauth token based authenticationsupports api versioningsupports automatic serialization of payload if your specification defines that an endpoint return json connexion will automatically serialize the return value for you and set the right content type in the http header with connexion you write the spec first connexion then call your python code handling the mapping from the specification to the code this incentivizes you to write the specification so that all of your developer can understand what your api doe even before you write a single line of code if multiple team depend on your apis you can use connexion to easily send them the documentation of your api this guarantee that your api will follow the specification that you wrote this is a different process from that offered by framework such a hug which generates a specification after you ve written the code some disadvantage of generating specification based on code is that they often end up lacking detail or mix your documentation with the code logic of your application zalando restful api guideline with api firstconnexion listed on swagger s websiteblog post crafting effective microservices in pythonapp and api option must be provided through the option argument old style option have been removed you must specify a form content type in consumes in order to consume form data the operation interface ha been formalized in the abstractoperation class the operation class ha been renamed to swagger operation array parameter deserialization now follows the swagger spec more closely in situation when a query parameter is passed multiple time and the collectionformat is either csv or pipe the right most value will be used for example q q will result in q the old behavior is available by setting the collectionformat to multi or by importing decorator uri parsing alwaysmultiuriparser and passing parser class alwaysmultiuriparser to your api the spec validator library ha changed from swagger spec validator to openapi spec validator error that previously raised swaggervalidationerror now raise the invalidspecification exception all spec validation error should be wrapped with invalidspecification support for nullable x nullable readonly and writeonly x writeonly ha been added to the standard json schema validator custom validators can now be specified on api level instead of app level added support for basic authentication and apikey authenticationif unsupported security requirement are defined or x tokeninfofunc x tokeninfourl is missing connexion now denies request instead of allowing access without security check accessing connexion request user flask request user is no longer supported use connexion context user insteadpython in your command line type place your api yaml inside a folder in the root path of your application e g swagger then run see the connexion pet store example application for a sample specification now you re able to run and use connexion connexion support one of the three oauth handling method see todo below with connexion the api security definition must include a x tokeninfourl or x tokeninfofunc or set tokeninfo url or tokeninfo func env var respectively x tokeninfourl must contain an url to validate and get the token information and x tokeninfofunc must contain a reference to a function used to obtain the token info when both x tokeninfourl and x tokeninfofunc are used connexion will prioritize the function method connexion expects to receive the oauth token in the authorization header field in the format described in rfc section this aspect represents a significant difference from the usual oauth flow connexion us jinja to allow specification parameterization through the argument parameter you can define specification argument for the application either globally via the connexion app constructor or for each specific api via the connexion app add api method when a value is provided both globally and on the api the api value will take precedence connexion us the operationid from each operation object to identify which python function should handle each url explicit routing if you provide this path in your specification post request to http myhost hello world it will be handled by the function hello world in the myapp api module optionally you can include x swagger router controller or x openapi router controller in your operation definition making operationid relative keep in mind that connexion follows how http method work in flask and therefore head request will be handled by the operationid specified under get in the specification if both method are supported connexion request method can be used to determine which request wa made to customize this behavior connexion can use alternative resolvers for example restyresolver the restyresolver will compose an operationid based on the path and http method of the endpoint in your specification restyresolver will give precedence to any operationid encountered in the specification it will also respect x router controller you can import and extend connexion resolver resolver to implement your own operationid and function resolution algorithm connexion automatically map the parameter defined in your endpoint specification to argument of your python view a named parameter and whenever possible with value casting simply define the endpoint s parameter with the same name a your view argument a an example say you have an endpoint specified a and the view function in this example connexion automatically recognizes that your view function expects an argument named message and assigns the value of the endpoint parameter message to your view function notein the openapi x x spec the requestbody doe not have a name by default it will be passed in a body you can optionally provide the x body name parameter in your requestbody or legacy position within the requestbody schema to override the name of the parameter that will be passed to your handler function warningwhen you define a parameter at your endpoint a not required and this argument doe not have default value in your python view you will get a missing positional argument exception whenever you call this endpoint without the parameter provide a default value for a named argument or use kwargs dict whenever possible connexion will try to parse your argument value and do type casting to related python native value the current available type casting are openapi typepython typeintegerintstringstrnumberfloatbooleanboolarraylistnullnoneobjectdictif you use the array type in the swagger definition you can define the collectionformat so that it won t be recognized connexion currently support collection format pipe and csv the default format is csv connexion is opinionated about how the uri is parsed for array type the default behavior for query parameter that have been defined multiple time is to use the right most value for example if you provide a uri with the the query string letter a b c letter d e f connexion will set letter d e f you can override this behavior by specifying the uri parser in the app or api option you can implement your own uri parsing behavior by inheriting from connexion decorator uri parsing abstracturiparser there are a handful of uri parser included with connection openapiuriparser default openapi this parser adheres to the openapi x x spec and us the style parameter query parameter are parsed from left to right so if a query parameter is defined twice then the right most definition will take precedence for example if you provided a uri with the query string letter a b c letter d e f and style simple then connexion will set letter d e f for additional information see openapi style value swagger uriparser default openapi this parser adheres to the swagger spec and will only join together multiple instance of the same query parameter if the collectionformat is set to multi query parameter are parsed from left to right so if a query parameter is defined twice then the right most definition win for example if you provided a uri with the query string letter a b c letter d e f and collectionformat csv then connexion will set letter d e f firstvalueuriparserthis parser behaves like the swagger uriparser except that it prefers the first defined value for example if you provided a uri with the query string letter a b c letter d e f and collectionformat csv hen connexion will set letter a b c alwaysmultiuriparserthis parser is backwards compatible with connexion x it join together multiple instance of the same query parameter connexion can apply strict parameter validation for query and form data parameter when this is enabled request that include parameter not defined in the swagger spec return a error you can enable it when adding the api to your application setting a base path is useful for versioned apis an example of a base path would be the in http myhost hello world if you are using openapi x x you set your base url path in the server block of the specification you can either specify a full url or just a relative path if you are using openapi you can define a basepath on the top level of your openapi specification if you don t want to include the base path in your specification you can provide it when adding the api to your application connexion make the openapi swagger specification in json format available from either swagger json for openapi or openapi json for openapi x x at the base path of the api for example if your base path wa then your spec would be available at openapi json you can disable serving the spec json at the application level you can also disable it at the api level when specifying http a the scheme in the api yaml file all the uris in the served swagger ui are http endpoint the problem the default server that run is a normal http server this mean that the swagger ui cannot be used to play with the api what is the correct way to start a http server when using connexion one way described by flask look like this however connexion doesn t provide an ssl context parameter this is because flask doesn t either but it us kwargs to send the parameter to the underlying werkzeug server the swagger ui for an api is available through pip extra you can install it with pip install connexion swagger ui it will be served up at base path ui where base path is the base path of the api you can disable the swagger ui at the application level you can also disable it at the api level if necessary you can explicitly specify the path to the directory with swagger ui to not use the connexion swagger ui distro in order to do this you should specify the following option if you wish to provide your own swagger ui distro note that connexion expects a jinja file called swagger ui index j in order to load the correct swagger json by default your index j file can use the openapi spec url jinja variable for this purpose additionally if you wish to use swagger ui x x it is also provided by installing connexion swagger ui and can be enabled like this by default connexion us the flask server for asynchronous application you can also use tornado a the http server to do this set your server to tornado you can use the flask wsgi app with any wsgi container e g using flask with uwsgi this is common you can use the aiohttp framework a server backend a well notealso check aiohttp handler example set up and run the installation code see the uwsgi documentation for more information additional information is available at connexion s documentation page a full changelog is maintained on the github release page we welcome your idea issue and pull request just follow the usual standard github practice you can find out more about how connexion work and where to apply your change by having a look at our architecture rst unless you description: cymem provides two small memory management helper for cython they make it easy to tie memory to a python object s life cycle so that the memory is freed when the object is garbage collected the most useful is cymem pool which act a a thin wrapper around the calloc function the pool object save the memory address internally and free them when the object is garbage collected typically you ll attach the pool to some cdef d class this is particularly handy for deeply nested structs which have complicated initialization function just pas the pool object into the initializer and you don t have to worry about freeing your struct at all all of the call to pool alloc will be automatically freed when the pool expires installation is via pip and requires cython before installing make sure that your pip setuptools and wheel are up to date let s say we want a sequence of sparse matrix we need fast access and a python list isn t performing well enough so we want a c array or c vector which mean we need the sparse matrix to be a c level struct it can t be a python class we can write this easily enough in cython we wrap the data structure in a python ref counted class at a low a level a we can given our performance constraint this allows u to allocate and free the memory in the cinit and dealloc cython special method however it s very easy to make mistake when writing the dealloc and sparse matrix free function leading to memory leak cymem prevents you from writing these deallocators at all instead you write a follows all that the pool class doe is remember the address it give out when the matrixarray object is garbage collected the pool object will also be garbage collected which trigger a call to pool dealloc the pool then free all of it into multiple smaller sample we shuffle the newly generated sub sample further to mix up sub sample from different image in the stream this us the compose method which take a function that map an interator over sample into another iterator over sample webdataset is just an instance of a standard iterabledataset it s a single threaded way of iterating over a dataset since image decompression and data augmentation can be compute intensive pytorch usually us the dataloader class to parallelize data loading and preprocessing webdataset is fully compatible with the standard dataloader the webdataset library contains a small wrapper that add a fluid interface to the dataloader and is otherwise identical this come in handy if you want to shuffle across dataset instance and allows you to whether you want to keep exact epoch exactly and only one sample from the dataset per epoch and whether your training framework can deal with unequal number of sample per node the simplest solution binary representation of data structure cbor file are particularly useful for large collection of very small sample data tuples short string etc writing cbor file is very easy of course you can these file directly and cbor file shard integrate fully into datapipeline with the cbors to sample function webdataset is an ideal solution for training on petascale datasets kept on high performance distributed data store like aistore aws s and google cloud compared to data center gpu server desktop machine have much slower network connection but training job on desktop machine often also use much smaller datasets webdataset also is very useful for such smaller datasets and it can easily be used for developing and testing on small datasets and then scaling up to large datasets by simply using more shard here are different usage scenario webdataset make it easy to use a single specification for your datasets and run your code without change in different environment if you write your code and reformats it to the best formatting that conforms to the style guide even if the original code didn t violate the style guide the idea is also similar to the gofmt tool for the go programming language end all holy war about formatting if the whole codebase of a project is simply piped through yapf whenever modification are made the style remains consistent throughout the project and there description: websocket client is a websocket client for python it provides access to low level apis for websockets websocket client implement version hybi of the websocket protocol this client doe not currently support the permessage deflate extension from rfc this project s documentation can be found at http websocket client readthedocs io please see the contribution guidelinesyou can use either python setup py install or pip install websocket client to install this module is tested on python there are several optional dependency that can be installed to enable specific websocket client feature while not a strict dependency rel is useful when using run forever with automatic reconnect install rel with pip install rel footnote some shell such a zsh require you to escape the and character with a check out the documentation s faq for additional guideline http websocket client readthedocs io en latest faq htmlknown issue with this library include lack of websocket compression support rfc and minimal threading documentation support the send and validate utf method can sometimes be bottleneck you can disable utf validation in this library and receive a performance enhancement with the skip utf validation parameter if you want to get better performance install wsaccel while websocket client doe not depend on wsaccel it will be used if available wsaccel double the speed of utf validation and offer a very minor performance boost when masking the payload data a part of the send process numpy used to be a suggested performance enhancement alternative but issue found it didn t help many more example are found in the example documentation most real world websockets situation involve longer lived connection the websocketapp run forever loop will automatically try to reconnect to an open websocket connection when a network connection is lost if it is provided with a dispatcher parameter and provides a variety of event based connection control run forever doe not automatically reconnect if the server close the websocket customizing behavior when the server close the websocket should be handled in the on close callback this example us rel for the dispatcher to provide automatic reconnection this is if you want to communicate a short message and disconnect immediately when done for example if you want to confirm that a websocket server is running and responds properly to a specific request

can also look up entity case insensitively without knowing which key the value may match for example the search end with the first match which is returned update to iso code update to iso code thanks to iso code pr clean up the normalization lower casing of value in index and search see pr http github com flyingcircusio pycountry pull for detailed discussion this also fixed issue smaller cleanup and build environment version bump pr python only cleanup and updated python minor version compatibility thanks djailla pr remove defunct bugtracker link from readme thanks jwilk p somewhat hilarious keyerror instead of doing the pythonic thing and returning none and allowing to customize the default there wa a bit of back and forth around this code in previous release specifically touching edge case to have the subdivision api behave reasonably although there doesn t seem to be one right way there anyway when preparing this release and reviewing and the other related issue and change from description: implement a topological sort algorithm from wikipedia in computer science a topological sort sometimes abbreviated topsort or toposort or topological ordering of a directed graph is a linear ordering of it vertex such that for every directed edge uv from vertex u to vertex v u come before v in the ordering the input to the toposort function is a dict describing the dependency among the input node each key is a dependent node the corresponding value is a set containing the dependent node note that toposort doe not care what the input node value mean it just compare them for equality the example here usually use integer but they could be any hashable type the interpretation of the input data here is if depends on depends on and depends on and and so on then in what order should we process the item such that all node are processed before any of their dependency and the answer is process and in any order then process and then process and then process note that and are returned first because they do not depend on anything they are then removed from consideration and then and don t depend on anything remaining this process continues until all node are returned or a circular dependency is detected a circular dependency will raise a cyclicdependencyerror which is derived from valueerror here depends on and depends on in addition the data attribute of the raised cyclicdependencyerror will contain a dict containing the subset of the input data involved in the circular dependency toposort data return an iterator describing the dependency among node in the input data each returned item will be a set each member of this set ha no dependency in this set or in any set previously returned toposort flatten data sort true like toposort data except that it return a list of all of the depend value in order if sort is true the returned node are sorted within each group before they are appended to the result note that this result is the same a the first example except that the result is flattened and within each set the node are sorted to test run python setup py test on python this also run the doctests

description: one of the holy grail of machine learning is to automate more and more of the feature engineering process pedro domingo a few useful thing to know about machine learning featuretools is a python library for automated feature engineering see the documentation for more information install with pipor from the conda forge channel on conda you can install add ons individually or all at once by runningupdate checker receive automatic notification of new featuretools releasesnlp primitive use natural language processing primitive tsfresh primitive use primitive from tsfresh within featuretoolssql automatic entityset generation from relational data stored in a sql database below is an example of using deep feature synthesis dfs to perform automated feature engineering in this example we apply dfs to a multi table dataset consisting of timestamped customer transaction featuretools can automatically create a single table of feature for any target dataframe we now have a feature vector for each customer that can be used for machine learning see the documentation on deep feature synthesis for more example featuretools contains many different type of built in primitive for creating feature if the primitive you need is not included featuretools also allows you to define your own custom primitive predict next purchaserepository notebookin this demonstration we use a multi table dataset of million online grocery order from instacart to predict what a customer will buy next we show how to generate feature with automated feature engineering and build an accurate machine learning pipeline using featuretools which can be reused for multiple prediction problem for more advanced user we show how to scale that pipeline to a large dataset using dask for more example of how to use featuretools check out our demo page the featuretools community welcome pull request instruction for testing and development are available here the featuretools community is happy to provide support to user of featuretools project support can be found in four place depending on the type of question if you use featuretools please consider citing the following paper james max kanter kalyan veeramachaneni deep feature synthesis towards automating data science endeavor ieee dsaa bibtex entry featuretools is an open source project maintained by alteryx to see the other open source project we re working on visit alteryx open source if building impactful data science pipeline is important to you or your business please get in touch

description: convert and manipulates common color representation rgb hsl web damn simple and pythonic way to manipulate color representation see example below full conversion between rgb hsl digit hex digit hex human colorone object color or bunch of single purpose function rgb hex hsl rgb web format that use the smallest representation between digit e g fa b c digit e g fbb fully spelled color e g white following w c color naming for compatible cs or html color specification smooth intuitive color scale generation choosing n color gradient can pick color for you to identify object of your application you don t need to download the git version of the code a colour is available on the pypi so you should be able to run if you have downloaded the git source then you could add the colour py directly to one of your site package thanks to a symlink or install the current version via traditional and if you don t have the git source but would like to get the latest master or branch from github you could also or even select a specific revision branch tag commit to get complete demo of each function please read the source code which is heavily documented and provide a lot of example in doctest format here is a reduced sample of a common usage scenario let s create blue color please note that all of these are equivalent example to create the red color several representation are accessible and their different part are also independently accessible a the different amount of red blue green in the rgb format or the hue saturation and luminance of the hsl representation a note on the hex property it ll return the smallest valid value when possible if you are only interested by the long value use hex l all of these property are read write so let s add some red to this color we might want to de saturate this color and of course the string conversion will give the web representation which is human or digit or digit hex representation depending which is usable you can get some color scale of variation between two color object quite easily here is the color scale of the rainbow between red and blue or the different amount of gray between black and white if you have to create graphical representation with color scale between red and green lime color is full green notice how naturally the yellow is displayed in human format and in the middle of the scale and that the quite unusual but compatible chartreuse color specification ha been used in place of the hexadecimal representation color comparison is a vast subject however it might seem quite straightforward for you colour us a configurable default way of comparing color that might suit your need the default comparison algorithm focus only on the web representation which is equivalent to comparing the long hex representation e g ff or to be more specific it is equivalent to compare the amount of red green and blue composition of the rgb representation each of these value being quantized to a value scale this default comparison is a practical and convenient way to measure the actual color equivalence on your screen or in your video card memory but this comparison wouldn t make the difference between a black red and a black blue which both are black but this is not the sole way to compare two color a i m quite lazy i m providing you a way to customize it to your need thus a you might have already guessed the sane default is rgb equivalence so here s how you could implement your unique comparison function note when comparing color only the equality function of the first color will be used thus but reverse operation is not equivalent a a side note whatever your custom equality function is it won t be used if you compare to anything else than a colour instance note that these instance would compare a equal to any other color but on another non colour object actually colour instance will politely enough leave the other side of the equality have a chance to decide of the output by executing it own eq so and inequality using ne are also polite sometimes you just want to pick a color for an object in your application often to visually identify this object thus the picked color should be the same for same object and different for different object of course although there s a tiny probability that different string yield the same color most of the time different input will produce different color you can customize your color picking algorithm by providing a picker a picker is a callable that take an object and return something that can be instantiated a a color by color you might want to use a particular picker but enforce how the picker will identify two object a the same or not so there s a pick key attribute that is provided and default a equivalent of hash method and if hash is not supported by your object it ll default to the str of your object salted with the class name thus please make sure your object is hashable or stringable before using the rgb color picker picking mechanism or provide another color picker nearly all python object are hashable by default so this shouldn t be an issue e g instance of object and subclass are hashable neither hash nor str are perfect solution so feel free to use pick key at color instantiation time to set your way to identify object for instance when choosing a pick key you should closely consider if you want your color to be consistent between run this is not the case with the last example or consistent with the content of your object if it is a mutable object default value of pick key and picker ensures that the same color will be attributed to same object between different run on different computer for most python object a you might have noticed there are few attribute that you might want to see attached to all of your color a equality for equality comparison support or picker pick key to configure your object color picker you can create a customized color factory thanks to the make color factory all color created thanks to customcolor class instead of the default one would get the specified attribute by default of course these are always instance of color class equality wa changed from normal default so this because the default equivalence of color wa set to hsl equivalence any suggestion or issue is welcome push request are very welcome please check out the guideline you can send any code i ll look at it and will integrate it myself in the code base and leave you a the author this process can take time and it ll take le time if you follow the following guideline check your code with pep or pylint try to stick to column wide separate your commits per smallest concern each commit should pas the test to allow easy bisect each functionality bugfix commit should contain the code test and doc prior minor commit with typographic or code cosmetic change are very welcome these should be tagged in their commit summary with minor the commit message should follow
