description: programmatically build and manage training datathe snorkel team is now focusing their effort on snorkel flow an end to end ai application development platform based on the core idea behind snorkel you can check it out here or join u in building it the snorkel project started at stanford in with a simple technical bet that it would increasingly be the training data not the model algorithm or infrastructure that decided whether a machine learning project succeeded or failed given this premise we set out to explore the radical idea that you could bring mathematical and system structure to the messy and often entirely manual process of training data creation and management starting by empowering user to programmatically label build and manage training data to say that the snorkel project succeeded and expanded beyond what we had ever expected would be an understatement the basic goal of a research repo like snorkel are to provide a minimum viable framework for testing and validating hypothesis four year later we ve been fortunate to do not just this but to develop and deploy early version of snorkel in partnership with some of the world s leading organization like google intel stanford medicine and many more author over thirty six peer reviewed publication on our finding around snorkel and related innovation in weak supervision modeling data augmentation multi task learning and more be included in course at top tier university support production deployment in system that you ve likely used in the last few hour and work with an amazing community of researcher and practitioner from industry medicine government academia and beyond however we realized increasingly from conversation with user in weekly office hour workshop online discussion and industry partner that the snorkel project wa just the very first step the idea behind snorkel change not just how you label training data but so much of the entire lifecycle and pipeline of building deploying and managing ml how user inject their knowledge how model are constructed trained inspected versioned and monitored how entire pipeline are developed iteratively and how the full set of stakeholder in any ml deployment from subject matter expert to ml engineer are incorporated into the process over the last year we have been building the platform to support this broader vision snorkel flow an end to end machine learning platform for developing and deploying ai application snorkel flow incorporates many of the concept of the snorkel project with a range of newer technique around weak supervision modeling data augmentation multi task learning data slicing and structuring monitoring and analysis and more all of which integrate in a way that is greater than the sum of it part and that we believe make ml truly faster more flexible and more practical than ever before moving forward we will be focusing our effort on snorkel flow we are extremely grateful for all of you description: this library is an implementation of the json ld specification in python json a specified in rfc is a simple language for representing object on the web linked data is a way of describing content across different document or web site web resource are described using iris and typically are dereferencable entity that may be used to find more information creating a web of knowledge json ld is intended to be a simple publishing method for expressing not only linked data in json but for adding semantics to existing json json ld is designed a a light weight syntax that can be used to express linked data it is primarily intended to be a way to express linked data in javascript and other web based programming environment it is also useful when building interoperable web service and when storing linked data in json based document storage engine it is practical and designed to be a simple a possible utilizing the large number of json parser and existing code that is in use today it is designed to be able to express key value pair rdf data rdfa data microformats data and microdata that is it support every major web based structured data model in use today the syntax doe not require many application to change their json but easily add meaning by adding context in a way that is either in band or out of band the syntax is designed to not disturb already deployed system running on json but provide a smooth migration path from json to json with added semantics finally the format is intended to be fast to parse fast to generate stream based and document based processing compatible and require a very small memory footprint in order to operate this library aim to conform with the following json ld w c candidate recommendation or newerjson ld processing algorithm and api w c candidate recommendation or newerjson ld framing w c candidate recommendation or newerworking group test suitethe test runner is often updated to note or skip newer test that are not yet supported python or later request optional aiohttp optional python or later pyld can be installed with a pip packagedefining a dependency on pyld will not pull in request or aiohttp if you need one of these for a document loader then either depend on the desired external library directly or define the requirement a pyld request or pyld aiohttp the default document loader for pyld us request in a production environment you may want to setup a custom loader that at a minimum set a timeout value you can also force request to use http set client cert disable verification or set other request parameter an asynchronous document loader using aiohttp is also available please note that this document loader limit asynchronicity to fetching document only the processing loop remain synchronous when no document loader is specified the default loader is set to request if request is not available the loader is set to aiohttp the fallback document loader is a dummy document loader that raise an exception on every invocation commercial support for this library is available upon request from digital bazaar support digitalbazaar com the source code for the python implementation of the json ld api is available at http github com digitalbazaar pyldthis library includes a sample testing utility which may be used to verify that change to the processor maintain the correct output to run the sample test you will need to get the test suite file by cloning the json ld api json ld framing and normalization repository hosted on github http github com w c json ld apihttps github com w c json ld framinghttps github com json ld normalizationif the suite repository are available a sibling directory of the pyld source directory then all the test can be run with the following if you want to test individual manifest jsonld file or directory containing a manifest jsonld then you can supply these file or directory a argument the test runner support different document loader by setting l request or l aiohttp the default document loader is set to request an earl report can be generated using the e or earl option

description: asyncio compatible timeout context manager the context manager is useful in case when you want to apply timeout logic around block of code or in case when asyncio wait for is not suitable also it s much faster than asyncio wait for because timeout doesn t create a new task the timeout delay loop none call return a context manager that cancel a block on timeout expiring if inner is executed faster than in second nothing happens otherwise inner is cancelled internally by sending asyncio cancellederror into but asyncio timeouterror is raised outside of context manager scope timeout parameter could be none for skipping timeout functionality alternatively timeout at when can be used for scheduling at the absolute time please note it is not posix time but a time with undefined starting base e g the time of the system power on context manager ha expired property for check if timeout happens exactly in context manager the property is true if inner execution is cancelled by timeout context manager if inner call explicitly raise timeouterror cm expired is false the scheduled deadline time is available a deadline property not finished yet timeout can be rescheduled by shift by or shift to method rescheduling is forbidden if the timeout is expired or after exit from async with code block the library is python only the module is written by andrew svetlov it s apache licensed and freely available

description: papermill is a tool for parameterizing executing and analyzing jupyter notebook papermill let you this open up new opportunity for how notebook can be used for example papermill take an opinionated approach to notebook parameterization and execution based on our experience using notebook at scale in data pipeline from the command line for all optional io dependency you can specify individual bundle like s or azure or use all to use black to format parameter you can add a an extra requires black this library currently support python version a minor python version are officially sunset by the python org papermill will similarly drop support in the future to parameterize your notebook designate a cell with the tag parameter papermill look for the parameter cell and treat this cell a default for the parameter passed in at execution time papermill will add a new cell tagged with injected parameter with input parameter in order to overwrite the value in parameter if no cell is tagged with parameter the injected cell will be inserted at the top of the notebook additionally if you rerun notebook through papermill and it will reuse the injected parameter cell from the prior run in this case papermill will replace the old injected parameter cell with the new run s input the two way to execute the notebook with parameter are through the python api and through the command line interface here s an example of a local notebook being executed and output to an amazon s account note if you use multiple aws account and you have properly configured your aws credential then you can specify which account to use by setting the aws profile environment variable at the command line for example in the above example two parameter are set alpha and l ratio using p parameter also work parameter value that look like booleans or number will be interpreted a such here are the different way user may set parameter using r or parameter raw user can set parameter one by one however unlike p the parameter will remain a string even if it may be interpreted a a number or boolean using f or parameter file user can provide a yaml file from which parameter value should be read using y or parameter yaml user can directly provide a yaml string containing parameter value using b or parameter base user can provide a yaml string base encoded containing parameter value when using yaml to pas argument through y b or f parameter value can be array or dictionary papermill support the following name handler for input and output path during execution local file system localhttp http protocol http http amazon web service aws s s azure azure datalake store azure blob store adl ab google cloud google cloud storage g read contributing md for guideline on how to setup a local development environment and make code change back to papermill for development guideline look in the development guide md file this should inform you on how to make particular addition to the code base we host the papermill documentation on readthedocs

description: september v june v see the example folder for notebook you can download or run on google colab this library contains module each of which can be used independently within your existing codebase or combined together for a complete train test workflow let s initialize a plain tripletmarginloss to compute the loss in your training loop pas in the embeddings computed by your model and the corresponding label the embeddings should have size n embedding size and the label should have size n where n is the batch size the tripletmarginloss computes all possible triplet within the batch based on the label you pas into it anchor positive pair are formed by embeddings that share the same label and anchor negative pair are formed by embeddings that have different label sometimes it can help to add a mining function in the above code the miner find positive and negative pair that it think are particularly difficult note that even though the tripletmarginloss operates on triplet it s still possible to pas in pair this is because the library automatically convert pair to triplet and triplet to pair when necessary loss function can be customized using distance reducer and regularizers in the diagram below a miner find the index of hard pair within a batch these are used to index into the distance matrix computed by the distance object for this diagram the loss function is pair based so it computes a loss per pair in addition a regularizer ha been supplied so a regularization loss is computed for each embedding in the batch the per pair and per element loss are passed to the reducer which in this diagram only keep loss with a high value the average are computed for the high valued pair and element loss and are then added together to obtain the final loss now here s an example of a customized tripletmarginloss this customized triplet loss ha the following property the tripletmarginloss is an embedding based or tuple based loss this mean that internally there is no real notion of class tuples pair or triplet are formed at each iteration based on the label it receives the label don t have to represent class they simply need to indicate the positive and negative relationship between the embeddings thus it is easy to use these loss function for unsupervised or self supervised learning for example the code below is a simplified version of the augmentation strategy commonly used in self supervision the dataset doe not come with any label instead the label are created in the training loop solely to indicate which embeddings are positive pair if you re interested in moco style self supervision take a look at the moco on cifar notebook it us crossbatchmemory to implement the momentum encoder queue which mean you can use any tuple loss and any tuple miner to extract hard sample from the queue if you re short of time and want a complete train test workflow check out the example google colab notebook to learn more about all of the above see the documentation other dependency numpy scikit learn tqdm torchvisionto get the latest dev version to install on window to install with evaluation and logging capability this will install the unofficial pypi version of faiss gpu plus record keeper and tensorboard to install with evaluation and logging capability cpu this will install the unofficial pypi version of faiss cpu plus record keeper and tensorboard to use the testing module you ll need faiss which can be installed via conda a well see the installation instruction for faiss see powerful benchmarker to view benchmark result and to use the benchmarking tool development is done on the dev branch unit test can be run with the default unittest library you can specify the test datatypes and test device a environment variable for example to test using float and float on the cpu to run a single test file instead of the entire test suite specify the file name code is formatted using black and isort thanks to the contributor who made pull request thank you to ser nam lim at facebook ai and my research advisor professor serge belongie this project began during my internship at facebook ai where i received valuable feedback from ser nam and his team of computer vision and machine learning engineer and research scientist in particular thanks to ashish shah and austin reiter for reviewing my code during it early stage of development this library contains code that ha been adapted and modified from the following great open source repos thanks to jeff musgrave for designing the logo if you d like to cite pytorch metric learning in your paper you can use this bibtex

automatically downloads source file when available will download and verify the source file for query document qrels etc when they are publicly available a they are needed a ci build check weekly to available instruction for dataset access when not publicly available provides instruction on how to get a copy of the data when it is not publicly available online e g when it requires a data usage agreement support for datasets big and small by using iterators support large datasets that may not fit into system memory such a clueweb fix known dataset issue for instance automatically corrects clueweb us checkpoint file to load document from source x faster than normal result are cached for even faster subsequent access fancy iter slicing sometimes it s helpful to be able to select range of data e g for processing document collection in parallel on multiple device efficient implementation of slicing operation allow for much faster dataset partitioning than using itertools slice available datasets include there are subset under each dataset for instance clueweb b trec misinfo provides the query and judgment from the trec misinformation track and msmarco document orca provides the orca dataset they tend to be organized with the document collection at the top level see the ir dataets doc ir datasets com for detail about each dataset it available subset and what data they provide when description: fugue is a unified interface for distributed computing that let user execute python panda and sql code on spark dask and ray without rewrite the most common use case are for a more comprehensive overview of fugue read this article fugue can be installed through pip or conda for example it also ha the following extra for example a common use case is notice that installing extra may not be necessary for example if you already installed spark or duckdb independently fugue is able to automatically enable the support for them the best way to get started with fugue is to work through the minute tutorial the tutorial can also be run in an interactive notebook environment through binder or docker note it run slow on binder because the machine on binder isn t powerful enough for a distributed framework such a spark parallel execution can become sequential so some of the performance comparison example will not give you the correct number alternatively you should get decent performance by running this docker image on your own machine for the api doc click herethe simplest way to use fugue is the transform function this let user parallelize the execution of a single function by bringing it to spark dask or ray in the example below the map letter to food function take in a mapping and applies it on a column this is just panda and python so far without fugue now the map letter to food function is brought to the spark execution engine by invoking the transform function of fugue the output schema params and engine are passed to the transform call the schema is needed because it s a requirement on spark a schema of below mean all input column are in the output this syntax is simpler cleaner and more maintainable than the pyspark equivalent at the same time no edits were made to the original panda based function to bring it to spark it is still usable on panda dataframes because the spark execution engine wa used the returned df is now a spark dataframe fugue transform also support dask ray and panda a execution engine a sql based language capable of expressing end to end workflow the map letter to food function above is used in the sql expression below this is how to use a python defined transformer along with the standard sql select statement for fuguesql we can change the engine by passing it to the run method fsql query mapping map dict str run spark there is an accompanying notebook extension for fuguesql that let user use the fsql cell magic the extension also provides syntax highlighting for fuguesql cell it work for both classic notebook and jupyter lab more detail can be found in the installation instruction by being an abstraction layer fugue can be used with a lot of other open source project seamlessly fugue can use the following project a backends fugue is available a a backend or can integrate with the following project view some of our latest conference presentation and content for a more complete list check the resource page in the tutorial feel free to message u on slack we also have contributing instruction

description: chex is a library of utility for helping to write reliable jax code this includes utils to help you can install the latest released version of chex from pypi via or you can install the latest development version from github dataclasses are a popular construct introduced by python to allow to easily specify typed data structure with minimal boilerplate code they are not however compatible with jax and dm tree out of the box in chex we provide a jax friendly dataclass implementation reusing python dataclasses chex implementation of dataclass register dataclasses a internal pytree node to ensure compatibility with jax data structure in addition we provide a class wrapper that expose dataclasses a collection mapping descendant which allows to process them e g un flatten in dm tree method a usual python dictionary see mappable dataclass docstring for more detail example note unlike standard python dataclasses chex dataclasses cannot be constructed using positional argument they support construction argument provided in the same format a the python dict constructor dataclasses can be converted to tuples with the from tuple and to tuple method if necessary one limitation of pytype annotation for jax is that they do not support the specification of devicearray rank shape or dtypes chex includes a number of function that allow flexible and concise specification of these property e g suppose you want to ensure that all tensor t t t have the same shape and that tensor t t have rank and or respectively more example see asserts py documentation to find all supported assertion if you cannot find a specific assertion please consider making a pull request or openning an issue on the bug tracker all chex assertion support the following optional kwargs for manipulating the emitted exception message for example the following code will raise a valueerror that includes a step number when params get polluted with nan or none chex divide all assertion into class static and value assertion static assertion use anything except concrete value of tensor example assert shape assert tree all equal dtypes assert max trace value assertion require access to tensor value which are not available during jax tracing see howjax primitive work thus such assertion need special treatment in a jitted code to enable value assertion in a jitted function it can be decorated with chex chexify wrapper example see this docstring for more detail on chex chexify jax re trace jit ted function every time the structure of passed argument change often this behavior is inadvertent and lead to a significant performance drop which is hard to debug chex assert max trace decorator asserts that the function is not re traced more than n time during program execution global trace counter can be cleared by calling chex clear trace counter this function be used to isolate unittests relying on chex assert max trace example can be used with jax pmap a well see howjax primitive work section for more information about tracing jax relies extensively on code transformation and compilation meaning that it can be hard to ensure that code is properly tested for instance just testing a python function using jax code will not cover the actual code path that is executed when jitted and that path will also differ whether the code is jitted for cpu gpu or tpu this ha been a source of obscure and hard to catch bug where xla change would lead to undesirable behaviour that however only manifest in one specific code transformation variant make it easy to ensure that unit test cover different variation of a function by providing a simple decorator that can be used to repeat any test under all or a subset of the relevant code transformation e g suppose you want to test the output of a function fn with or without jit you can use chex variant to run the test with both the jitted and non jitted version of the function by simply decorating a test method with chex variant and then using self variant fn in place of fn in the body of the test if you define the function in the test method you may also use self variant a a decorator in the function definition for example example of parameterized test chex currently support the following variant see documentation in variant py for more detail on the supported variant more example can be found in variant test py test class that use chex variant must inherit from chex testcase or any other base class that unrolls test generator within testcase e g absl testing parameterized testcase jax vmap all variant can be applied to a vmapped function please see an example in variant test py test vmapped fn named params and test pmap vmapped fn chex all variant you can get all supported variant by using the decorator chex all variant with pmap variant jax pmap fn doc performs parallel map of fn onto multiple device since most test run in a single device environment i e having access to a single cpu or gpu in which case jax pmap is a functional equivalent to jax jit with pmap variant is skipped by default although it work fine with a single device below we describe a way to properly test fn if it is supposed to be used in multi device environment tpus or multiple cpu gpus to disable skipping with pmap variant in case of a single device add chex skip pmap variant if single device false to your test command debugging in jax is made more difficult by code transformation such a jit and pmap which introduce optimization that make code hard to inspect and trace it can also be difficult to disable those transformation during debugging a they can be called at several place in the underlying code chex provides tool to globally replace jax jit with a no op transformation and jax pmap with a non parallel jax vmap in order to more easily debug code in a single device context for example you can use chex to fake pmap and have it replaced with a vmap this can be achieved by wrapping your code with a context manager the same functionality can also be invoked with start and stop in addition you can fake a real multi device test environment with a multi threaded cpu see section faking multi device test environment for more detail see documentation in fake py and example in fake test py for more detail in situation where you do not have easy access to multiple device you can still test parallel computation using single device multi threading in particular one can force xla to use a single cpu s thread a separate device i e to fake a real multi device environment with a multi threaded one these two option are theoretically equivalent from xla perspective because they expose the same interface and use identical abstraction chex ha a flag chex n cpu device that specifies a number of cpu thread to use a xla device to set up a multi threaded xla environment for absl test define setupmodule function in your test module now you can launch your test with python test py chex n cpu device n to run it in multi device regime note that all test within a module will have an access to n device more example can be found in variant test py fake test py and fake set n cpu device test py chex come with a small utility that allows you to package a collection of dimension size into a single object the basic idea is string lookup are translated integer tuples for instance let s say batch size sequence len and embedding dim thenyou can also assign dimension size dynamically a follows for more example see chex dimension documentation this repository is part of the deepmind jax description: colab walkthrough arxivsidechainnet is a protein structure prediction dataset that directly extends proteinnet by mohammed alquraishi specifically sidechainnet add measurement for protein angle and coordinate that describe the complete all atom protein structure backbone and sidechain excluding hydrogen instead of the protein backbone alone this repository provides the following l reperesents the length of any given protein in the dataset secondary structure is acquired from proteinnet for training set only blank character are added by sidechainnet to refer to unmatched amino acid after alignment added january sidechainnet explicitly includes oxygen atom a part of the backbone coordinate data in contrast to proteinnet which only includes the primary n c alpha c atom stored a string value in the underlying sidechainnet data dictionary stored a string value in the underlying sidechainnet data dictionary includes a for each residue that ha been modified to a standard residue according to the mapping in sidechainnet utils measure allowed nonstd residue e g selenomethionine methionine pip install sidechainnetin it most basic form sidechainnet is stored a a python dictionary organized by train validation and test split these split are identical to those described in proteinnet within each train validation test split in sidechainnet is another dictionary mapping data entry type seq ang etc to a list containing this data type for every protein in the example below seq i ang i all refer to the ith protein in the dataset by default the load function downloads the data from the web into the current directory and load it a a python dictionary if the data already exists locally it read it from disk other than the requirement that the data must be loaded using python this method of data loading is agnostic to any downstream analysis the easiest way to interact with sidechainnet is most likely by using the scndataset and scnprotein object available feature additionally all of the attribute below are available directly from the scnprotein object the load function can also be used to load sidechainnet data a a dictionary of torch utils data dataloader object pytorch dataloaders make it simple to iterate over dataset item for training machine learning model this method is recommended for using sidechainnet data with pytorch for more information on the batch variable see the section using sidechainnet to train an all atom protein structure prediction model below by default the provided dataloaders use a custom batching method that randomly generates batch of protein of similar length for faster training it generates larger batch when the average length of protein in the batch is small and smaller batch when the protein are large the probability of selecting small length batch is decreased so that each protein in sidechainnet is included in a batch with equal probability see dynamic batching and collate fn argument for more information on modifying this behavior in the example below model input is a collated tensor containing sequence and pssm information an important component of this work is the inclusion of both angular and d coordinate representation of each protein researcher who develop method that rely on angular representation may be interested in converting this information into d coordinate for this reason sidechainnet provides a method to convert the angle it provides into cartesian coordinate in the below example angle is a numpy matrix or torch tensor following the same organization a the numpy angle matrix provided in sidechainnet sequence is a string representing the protein s amino acid sequence sidechainnet also make it easy to visualize both existing and predicted all atom protein structure these visualization are available a pdb file py dmol view object and graphic library transmission format gltf file example of each are included below the pdb format is a typical format for representing protein structure and can be opened in software tool like pymol py dmol built on dmol j enables user to visualize and interact with protein structure on the web and in jupyter notebook via an open source object oriented and hardware accelerated javascript library finally gltf file despite their larger size can be convenient for visualizing protein on the web or in context where other protein visualization tool are not supported below is an outline of how to use this repository for machine learning model training assuming you have a predictive model variable model and a loss function loss fn used to evaluate your model you can load sidechainnet using our dataloaders and begin training the batch variable above is a collection namedtuple that ha the following attribute if you would like to reproduce our work or make modification addition to the dataset please see the example we provide in our colab walkthrough in simple term you will need to call scn create with the desired casp proteinnet information or provide a list of proteinnet formatted id to scn create custom please note that since some data is acquired from proteinnet directly e g position specific scoring matrix protein entry will exclude this data if it wa not previously available in proteinnet thanks to mohammed alquraishi for his inspiring work on protein structure prediction thanks also to jeppe hallgren for his development of a proteinnet text record parser which i have used in part here this work is supported by r gm from the national institute of general medical science is supported in part by the university of pittsburgh center for research computing through the resource provided and by nih t training grant t eb a part of the hhmi nibib interface initiative project structure continuous integration doc testing based on the computational molecular science python cookiecutter version computational biology skill seminar u c berkeley may copyright c jonathan king

description: llvmlite is a project originally tailored for numba s need using the following approach a small c wrapper around the part of the llvm c api we need that are not already exposed by the llvm c api a ctypes python wrapper around the c api a pure python implementation of the subset of the llvm ir builder that we need for numba the old llvmpy binding expose a lot of llvm apis but the mapping of c style memory management to python is error prone numba and many jit compiler do not need a full llvm api only the ir builder optimizer and jit compiler apis are necessary the ir builder is pure python code and decoupled from llvm s frequently changing c apis materializing a llvm module call llvm s ir parser which provides better error message than step by step ir building through the c api no more segfaults or process abort most of llvmlite us the llvm c api which is small but very stable low maintenance when changing llvm version the binding is not a python c extension but a plain dll accessed using ctypes no need to wrestle with python s compiler requirement and c compatibility the python binding layer ha sane memory management llvmlite is quite faster than llvmpy s thanks to a much simpler architeture the numba test suite is twice faster than it wa the llvmlite llvmpy namespace provides a minimal llvmpy compatibility layer llvmlite work with python and greater a of version llvmlite requires llvm x x on all architectureshistorical compatibility table llvmlite versionscompatible llvm version x x x x for aarch only x x x x x x x x x x x x xyou ll find the documentation at http llvmlite pydata orgwe recommend you use the binary provided by the numba team for the conda package manager you can find them in numba s anaconda org channel for example or simply the official llvmlite package provided in the anaconda distribution if you don t want to use our pre built package you can compile and install llvmlite yourself the documentation will teach you how http llvmlite pydata org en latest install index html

description: they say a good example is worth page of api documentation a million directive or a thousand word well they probably lie but here s an example anyway there now you ve baked a state machine into narcolepticsuperhero let s take him her it out for a spin while we cannot read the mind of the actual batman we surely can visualize the current state of our narcolepticsuperhero have a look at the diagram extension if you want to know how getting a state machine up and running is pretty simple let s say you have the object lump an instance of class matter and you want to manage it state you can initialize a minimal working state machine bound to lump like this i say minimal because while this state machine is technically operational it doesn t actually do anything it start in the solid state but won t ever move into another state because no transition are defined yet let s try again notice the shiny new method attached to the matter instance evaporate ionize etc each method trigger the corresponding transition you don t have to explicitly define these method anywhere the name of each transition is bound to the model passed to the machine initializer in this case lump to be more precise your model should not already contain method with the same name a event trigger since transition will only attach convenience method to your model if the spot is not already taken if you want to modify that behaviour have a look at the faq furthermore there is a method called trigger now attached to your model if it hasn t been there before this method let you execute transition by name in case dynamic triggering is required the soul of any good state machine and of many bad one no doubt is a set of state above we defined the valid model state by passing a list of string to the machine initializer but internally state are actually represented a state object you can initialize and modify state in a number of way specifically you can the following snippet illustrate several way to achieve the same goal state are initialized once when added to the machine and will persist until they are removed from it in other word if you alter the attribute of a state object this change will not be reset the next time you enter that state have a look at how to extend state feature in case you require some other behaviour a state can also be associated with a list of enter and exit callback which are called whenever the state machine enters or leaf that state you can specify callback during initialization by passing them to a state object constructor in a state property dictionary or add them later for convenience whenever a new state is added to a machine the method on enter state name and on exit state name are dynamically created on the machine not on the model which allow you to dynamically add new enter and exit callback later if you need them note that on enter state name callback will not fire when a machine is first initialized for example if you have an on enter a callback defined and initialize the machine with initial a on enter a will not be fired until the next time you enter state a if you need to make sure on enter a fire at initialization you can simply create a dummy initial state and then explicitly call to a inside the init method in addition to passing in callback when initializing a state or adding them dynamically it s also possible to define callback in the model class itself which may increase code clarity for example now any time lump transition to state a the on enter a method defined in the matter class will fire you can always check the current state of the model by either and if you want to retrieve the actual state object for the current state you can do that through the machine instance s get state method if you d like you can choose your own state attribute name by passing the model attribute argument while initializing the machine this will also change the name of is state name to is model attribute state name though similarly auto transition will be named to model attribute state name instead of to state name this is done to allow multiple machine to work on the same model with individual state attribute name so far we have seen how we can give state name and use these name to work with our state machine if you favour stricter typing and more ide code completion or you just can t type sesquipedalophobia any longer because the word scare you using enumeration might be what you are looking for you can mix enums and string if you like e g state red orange state yellow state green but note that internally transition will still handle state by name enum enum name thus it is not possible to have the state green and state green at the same time some of the above example already illustrate the use of transition in passing but here we ll explore them in more detail a with state each transition is represented internally a it own object an instance of class transition the quickest way to initialize a set of transition is to pas a dictionary or list of dictionary to the machine initializer we already saw this above defining transition in dictionary ha the benefit of clarity but can be cumbersome if you re after brevity you might choose to define transition using list just make sure that the element in each list are in the same order a the positional argument in the transition initialization i e trigger source destination etc the following list of list is functionally equivalent to the list of dictionary above alternatively you can add transition to a machine after initialization the trigger argument defines the name of the new triggering method that get attached to the base model when this method is called it will try to execute the transition by default calling an invalid trigger will raise an exception this behavior is generally desirable since it help alert you to problem in your code but in some case you might want to silently ignore invalid trigger you can do this by setting ignore invalid trigger true either on a state by state basis or globally for all state if you need to know which transition are valid from a certain state you can use get trigger in addition to any transition added explicitly a to state method is created automatically whenever a state is added to a machine instance this method transition to the target state no matter which state the machine is currently in if you desire you can disable this behavior by setting auto transition false in the machine initializer a given trigger can be attached to multiple transition some of which can potentially begin or end in the same state for example in this case calling transmogrify will set the model s state to solid if it s currently plasma and set it to plasma otherwise note that only the first matching transition will execute thus the transition defined in the last line above won t do anything you can also make a trigger cause a transition from all state to a particular destination by using the wildcard note that wildcard transition will only apply to state that exist at the time of the add transition call calling a wildcard based transition when the model is in a state added after the transition wa defined will elicit an invalid transition message and will not transition to the target state a reflexive trigger trigger that ha the same state a source and destination can easily be added specifying a destination this is handy if the same reflexive trigger should be added to multiple state for example this will add reflexive transition for all three state with touch a trigger and with change shape executed after each trigger in contrast to reflexive transition internal transition will never actually leave the state this mean that transition related callback such a before or after will be processed while state related callback exit or enter will not to define a transition to be internal set the destination to none a common desire is for state transition to follow a strict linear sequence for instance given state a b c you might want valid transition for a b b c and c a but no other pair to facilitate this behavior transition provides an add ordered transition method in the machine class the default behaviour in transition is to process event instantly this mean event within an on enter method will be processed before callback bound to after are called the execution order of this example isif queued processing is enabled a transition will be finished before the next transition is triggered this result inimportant note when processing event in a queue the trigger call will always return true since there is no way to determine at queuing time whether a transition involving queued call will ultimately complete successfully this is true even when only a single event is processed when a model is removed from the machine transition will also remove all related event from the queue sometimes you only want a particular transition to execute if a specific condition occurs you can do this by passing a method or list of method in the condition argument in the above example calling heat when the model is in state solid will transition to state gas if is flammable return true otherwise it will transition to state liquid if is really hot return true for convenience there s also an unless argument that behaves exactly like condition but inverted in this case the model would transition from solid to gas whenever heat fire provided that both is flammable and is really hot return false note that condition checking method will passively receive optional argument and or data object passed to triggering method for instance the following call would pas the temp optional kwarg to the is flammable check possibly wrapped in an eventdata instance for more on this see the passing data section below if you want to check whether a transition is possible before you execute it look before you leap you can use may trigger name convenience function that have been attached to your model this will execute all prepare callback and evaluate the condition assigned to the potential transition transition check can also be used when a transition s destination is not available yet you can attach callback to transition a well a state every transition ha before and after attribute that contain a list of method to call before and after the transition executes there is also a prepare callback that is executed a soon a a transition start before any condition are checked or other callback are executed note that prepare will not be called unless the current state is a valid source for the named transition default action meant to be executed before or after every transition can be passed to machine during initialization with before state change and after state change respectively there are also two keywords for callback which should be executed independently a of how many transition are possible b if any transition succeeds and c even if an error is raised during the execution of some other callback callback passed to machine with prepare event will be executed once before processing possible transition and their individual prepare callback take place callback of finalize event will be executed regardless of the success of the processed transition note that if an error occurred it will be attached to event data a error and can be retrieved with send event true sometimes thing just don t work out a intended and we need to handle exception and clean up the mess to keep thing going we can pas callback to on exception to do this a you have probably already realized the standard way of passing callables to state condition and transition is by name when processing callback and condition transition will use their name to retrieve the related callable from the model if the method cannot be retrieved and it contains dot transition will treat the name a a path to a module function and try to import it alternatively you can pas name of property or attribute they will be wrapped into function but cannot receive event data for obvious reason you can also pas callables such a bound function directly a mentioned earlier you can also pas list tuples of callables name to the callback parameter callback will be executed in the order they were added the callable resolution is done in machine resolve callable this method can be overridden in case more complex callable resolution strategy are required examplein summary there are currently three way to trigger event you can call a model s convenience function like lump melt execute trigger by name such a lump trigger melt or dispatch event on multiple model with machine dispatch melt see section about multiple model in alternative initialization pattern callback on transition are then executed in the following order if any callback raise an exception the processing of callback is not continued this mean that when an error occurs before the transition in state on exit or earlier it is halted in case there is a raise after the transition ha been conducted in state on enter or later the state change persists and no rollback is happening callback specified in machine finalize event will always be executed unless the exception is raised by a finalizing callback itself note that each callback sequence ha to be finished before the next stage is executed blocking callback will halt the execution order and therefore block the trigger or dispatch call itself if you want callback to be executed in parallel you could have a look at the extension asyncmachine for asynchronous processing or lockedmachine for threading sometimes you need to pas the callback function registered at machine initialization some data that reflects the model s current state transition allows you to do this in two different way first the default you can pas any positional or keyword argument directly to the trigger method created when you call add transition you can pas any number of argument you like to the trigger there is one important limitation to this approach every callback function triggered by the state transition must be able to handle all of the argument this may cause problem if the callback each expect somewhat different data to get around this transition support an alternate method for sending data if you set send event true at machine initialization all argument to the trigger will be wrapped in an eventdata instance and passed on to every callback the eventdata object also maintains internal reference to the source state model transition machine and trigger associated with the event in case you need to access these for anything in all of the example so far we ve attached a new machine instance to a separate model lump an instance of class matter while this separation keep thing tidy because you don t have to monkey patch a whole bunch of new method into the matter class it can also get annoying since it requires you to keep track of which method are called on the state machine and which one are called on the model that the state machine is bound to e g lump on enter statea v machine add transition fortunately transition is flexible and support two other initialization pattern first you can create a standalone state machine that doesn t require another model at all simply omit the model argument during initialization if you initialize the machine this way you can then attach all triggering event like evaporate sublimate etc and all callback function directly to the machine instance this approach ha the benefit of consolidating all of the state machine functionality in one place but can feel a little bit unnatural if you think state logic should be contained within the model itself rather than in a separate controller an alternative potentially better approach is to have the model inherit from the machine class transition is designed to support inheritance seamlessly just be sure to override class machine s init method here you get to consolidate all state machine functionality into your existing model which often feel more natural than sticking all of the functionality we want in a separate standalone machine instance a machine can handle multiple model which can be passed a a list like machine model model model in case where you want to add model a well a the machine instance itself you can pas the class variable placeholder string machine self literal during initialization like machine model machine self literal model you description: freezegun is a library that allows your python test to travel through time by mocking the datetime module once the decorator or context manager have been invoked all call to datetime datetime now datetime datetime utcnow datetime date today time time time localtime time gmtime and time strftime will return the time that ha been frozen time monotonic and time perf counter will also be frozen but a usual it make no guarantee about their absolute value only their change over time freezegun us dateutil behind the scene so you can have nice looking datetimes freezegun is able to handle function and generator object freezegun ha an additional tick argument which will restart time at the given value but then time will keep ticking this is an alternative to the default parameter which will keep time stopped freezegun ha an additional auto tick second argument which will autoincrement the value every time by the given amount from the start value this is an alternative to the default parameter which will keep time stopped note that given auto tick second the tick parameter will be ignored freezegun allows for the time to be manually forwarded a well freezegun allows moving time to specific date parameter for move to can be any valid freeze time date string date datetime note that freezegun will not modify default argument the following code will print the current date see here for why to install freezegun simply on debian system sometimes it s desired to ignore freezegun behaviour for particular package i e library it s possible to ignore them for a single invocation by default freezegun ignores following package it s possible to set your own default ignore list please note this will override default ignore list if you want to extend existing default please use

description: perlin noise is ubiquitous in modern cgi used for procedural texturing animation and enhancing realism perlin noise ha been called the salt of procedural content perlin noise is a type of gradient noise smoothly interpolating across a pseudo random matrix of value the noise library includes native code implementation of perlin improved noise and perlin simplex noise it also includes a fast implementation of perlin noise in glsl for use in opengl shaders the shader code and many of the included example require pyglet http www pyglet org the native code noise function themselves do not however the perlin improved noise function can also generate fbm fractal brownian motion noise by combining multiple octave of perlin noise shader function for convenient generation of turbulent noise are also included appveyor support for window build thanks to federico tomassetti fix msvc compatibility thanks to christoph gohlke add d simplex noise tiling for d simplex noise and parameterized lacunaritysee change txt for more detail

description: a girder plugin for exposing slicer execution model cli over the web using docker and girder worker slicer cli web is both a girder plugin and a girder worker plugin it allows dockerized task to be run from the girder user interface in linux with python or prerequisite an appropriate version of python must be installed mongodb must be installed and running rabbitmq or another broker is needed to use girder worker docker must be installed and the current user must be part of the docker group to use girder to use girder worker the first time you start girder you ll need to configure it with at least one user and one assetstore see the girder documentation additionally it is recommended that you install some dockerized task such a the histomicstk algorithm this can be done going to the admin console plugins slicer cli web setting set a default task upload folder then import the dsarchive histomicstk latest docker image when installed in girder an admin user can go to the admin console plugins slicer cli web to add docker image select a docker image and an existing folder and then select import image slicer cli web will pull the docker image if it is not available on the girder machine for each docker image that is imported a folder is created with the image tag within this folder a subfolder is created with the image version the subfolder will have one item per cli that the docker image report these item can be moved after they have been imported just like standard girder item when you visit the item page of an imported cli an extra configure task section is shown you can set all of the input for the cli and indicate where output file should be stored selecting run task will have girder worker execute the cli see the job panel for progress and error message slicer cli web executes program from docker image any docker image can be used that complies with some basic response from it entrypoint specifically when a docker image is invoked like it need to respond with with a json dictionary of cli where the key of this dictionary are the name of the cli see cli list json for an example each available cli need to report what it take a input and output when the docker image is invoked like it need to return an xml specification to stdout see example xml for an example the xml must conform to the slicer execution schema with a few minor addition some type image file transform geometry table directory item can have a reference property when image file item directory are used with girder if the reference property is girder id then value will be passed a a girder id string rather than converted to a girder resource the region type can have a coordinatesystem property the region type ha an optional shape property that is a comma separated list of value that can include default rectangle polygon and multipolygon in the official schema region is a vector of six value of the form x y z rx ry rz defining a rectangle based on it center and radius in each of three dimension this is the default shape the rectangle shape allows a vector of four value defining a rectangle of the form x y width height where x y is the left and top of the rectangle in pixel coordinate many algorithm that accept this value accept a a default to specify the whole conceptual space the polygon shape allows for a list of x y value polygon must always have at least four point so that the vector of value cannot be confused with the default repeat the first vertex at the end to specify a triangle multipolygon allow multiple polygon or hole definition are specified by separating coordinate by this prohibits from being a coordinate within a polygon some input type image file item directory can have defaultnamematch defaultpathmatch and defaultrelativepath property the first two are regular expression designed to give a ui a value to match to prepopulate default value from file or path that match the regex defaultnamematch is intended to match the final path element whereas defaultpathmatch is used on the entire path a a combined string defaultrelativepath is used to find a value that ha a path relative to some base in the girder ui this might be from an item input type can have a datalist property if this is present when the cli is first loaded or possibly periodically after parameter have been changed the cli may be called with optional parameter the cli is expected to return a new line separated list of value that can be used a recommended input a an example a string input might have a datalist of enumerate option the cli would be called with the existing parameter plus the extra parameter specified by datalist if the result is sensible the input control would expose this list to the user the datalist property is a json encoded dictionary that override other parameter this should override parameter that aren t needed to be resolved to produce the datalist e g input and output file a that will speed up the call the cli should respond to the modified call with a response that contains multiple element some text element value that will be the suggested data for the control there are some special string parameter that if unspecified or blank are autopopulated string parameter with the name of girderapiurl and girdertoken are populated with the appropriate url and token so that a running job could use girder client to communicate with girder internally the ctk cli module is used this ha two difference from the slicer execution schema that are technically bug enumeration have bare element under the appropriate parent tag that is instead of a structure like string enumeration enumeration element value element element value element enumeration string enumeration the enumeration tag is omitted string enumeration element value element element value element string enumeration booleans specify a true or false value after the flag or long flag the slicer execution schema state that booleans should be false by default and the presense of the flag should make them true the ctk cli specifies that they take a single true or false parameter this doesn t change the xml it cahnges what is passed to the cli instead of passing longflag to set the flag to true longflag true must be passed the response from a docker image invoked with the list cli option need to be a json response returning a single object the object must contain a key for each cli each key ha a value used to parse or handle the cli here is a commented example each exposed cli is added a an endpoint using the rest path of slicer cli web docker image tag and version cli command run and also using the rest path of slicer cli web internal item id run where docker image tag and version is the combined tag and version with slash colon and at sign replaced by underscore all command line parameter can be passed a endpoint query parameter input item folder and file are specified by their girder id input image are specified by a girder file id output file are specified by name and with an associated parameter with the same name plus a folder suffix with a girder folder id the small example cli docker image can be built locally via docker build force rm t girder slicer cli web small or pulled from docker hub all cli that take any single item image or file a input can be run on a set of such resource from a single directory for non batch processing the id of the image item or file is passed to param for batch processing the id of a folder is passed to param folder and a regular expression is passed to param all item in that folder whose name match the regex are processed for image only item that contain large image are considered for file the first file in each considered item is used if two input have batch specification there must be a one to one correspondence between the each of the list of item determined by the folder id and regular expression all of the list are enumerated sorted by the lower case item name when running a batch job a parent job initiate ordinary non batch job the parent job will only start another child job when the most recent child job is no longer waiting to start this allows non batch job or multiple batch job child to naturally interleave the parent job can be canceled which will stop it from scheduling any more child job any cli parameter that take a value that isn t a girder resource identifer can be specified with a jinja style template string for instance instead of typing an explicit output file name one can specify something like title reference base now extension if this were being run on a task called radial blur on an image called sampleimage tiff where the output image referenced the image image and had a list of file extension starting with png this would end up being converted to the value radial blur sampleimage png the following template value are handled identically for all parameter title the displayed cli task title task the internal task name this usually doesn t have space in it image the tag of the docker image used for the task now the local time the job started in the form yyyymmdd hhmmss you can use yyyy mm dd hh mm s for the four digit year and two digit month day hour minute and second parameter name of cli parameter any parameter that isn t templated can be referenced by it name for instance in example in the small docker cli in this repo parameter stringchoice would get replaced by the value passed to the stringchoice parameter parameter name of cli parameter base is the same a the previous item except that if the right most part of the parameter look like a file extension it is removed this can be used to get the base name of file parameter there are also template value specific to individual parameter name the name of this parameter this usually doesn t have any space in it label the label of the is parameter this is what is displayed in the user interface description the description of the parameter index the index if any of the parameter default the default value if any of the parameter extension the first entry in the fileextension value of the parameter if any reference if the parameter ha a reference to another parameter this return that parameter s value it is equivalent to parameter reference reference base the reference value mentioned previously striped of the right most file extension if the local server environment ha any environment variable that begin with slicer cli web these are accessible in the template a env name for instance slicer cli web dask server would be accessible a env dask server

description: this library provides a fast standalone way to read and write warc format commonly used in web archive support python and python using six the only external dependency warcio support reading and writing of warc file compliant with both the warc and warc iso standard install with pip install warciothis library is a spin off of the warc reading and writing component of the pywb high fidelity replay library a key component of webrecorderthe library is designed for fast low level access to web archival content oriented around a stream of warc record rather than file a key feature of the library is to be able to iterate over a stream of warc record using the archiveiterator it includes the following feature reading a warc warc or arc streamon the fly arc to warc record conversiondecompressing and de chunking http payload content stored in warc arc file for example the following print the the url for each warc response record the stream object could be a file on disk or a remote network stream the archiveiterator read the warc content in a single pas the record is represented by an arcwarcrecord object which contains the format arc or warc record type the record header http header if any and raw stream for reading the payload the raw stream can be used to read the rest of the payload directly a special arcwarcrecord content stream function provides a stream that automatically decompresses and de chunk the http payload if it is compressed and or transfer encoding chunked the library provides support for reading but not writing arc file the arc format is legacy but is important to support in a consistent matter the archiveiterator can equally iterate over arc and warc file to emit arcwarcrecord object the special arc warc option convert arc record to warcs on the fly allowing for them to be accessed using the same api special warciterator and arciterator subclass of archiveiterator are also available to read only warc or only arc file for example here is a snippet for reading an arc and a warc using the same api the example stream a warc and arc file over http using request printing the warcinfo record or arc header and any response record or all arc record that contain html starting with warcio introduces a way to capture http s traffic directly to a warc file by monkey patching python s http client library this approach work well with the popular request library often used to fetch http s content note that request must be imported after the capture http module fetching the url http example com while capturing the response and request into a gzip compressed warc file named example warc gz can be done with the following four line the warc example warc gz will contain two record the response is written first then the request to write to a default in memory buffer bufferwarcwriter don t specify a filename using with capture http a writer additional request in the capture http context and will be appended to the warc a expected the warc ip address header will also be added for each record if the ip address is available the following example similar to a unit test from the test suite demonstrates the resulting record created with capture http the library provides a simple and extensible interface for writing standard compliant warc file the library come with a basic warcwriter class for writing to a single warc file and bufferwarcwriter for writing to an in memory buffer the basewarcwriter can be extended to support more complex operation there is no support for writing legacy arc file for more flexibility such a to use a custom warcwriter class the above example can be written a by default warcio creates warc record for maximum compatibility with existing tool to create warc record simply specify the warc version a follows when using warc the main difference is that the warc date timestamp header will be written with microsecond precision while warc only support second precision warc warc when capturing via http it is possible to provide a custom filter function which can be used to determine if a particular request and response record should be written to the warc file or skipped the filter function is called with the request and response record before they are written and can be used to substitute a different record for example a revisit instead of a response or to skip writing altogether by returning nothing a shown below please refer to test test capture http py for additional example of capturing request traffic to warc before this wa the primary method for fetching a url and then writing to a warc this process is a bit more verbose but provides for full control of warc creation and avoid monkey patching the following example load http example com creates a warc response record and writes it gzip compressed to example warc gz the block and payload digest are computed automatically creating warcinfo and revisit recordswriting response and request record togetherwriting custom warc recordsreading a full warc record from a streamplease refer to warcwriter py and test test writer py for additional example the library currently ship with a few simple command line tool the warcio index cmd will print a simple index of the record in the warc file a newline delimited json line ndjson warc header field to include in the index can be specified via the f flag and are included in the json block in order for convenience http header field can be included by prefixing them with the prefix http the special field offset refers to the record offset within the warc file note this library doe not produce cdx or cdxj format index often associated with web archive to create these index please see the cdxj indexer tool which extends warcio indexing to provide this functionality the warcio check command will check the payload and block digest of warc record if possible an exit value of indicates a failure warcio check v will print verbose output for each record in the warc file the recompress command allows for re compressing or normalizing warc or arc file to a record compressed gzipped warc file each warc record is compressed individually and concatenated this is the canonical warc storage format used by webrecorder and other web archiving institution and usually stored with a warc gz extension it can be used to compress an uncompressed warc convert any arc file to a compressed warc fix an improperly compressed warc file eg a warc compressed entirely instead of by record the extract command provides a way to extract either the warc and http header and or payload of a warc record to stdout given a warc filename and an offset extract will print the decompressed record at that offset in the file to stdoutspecifying payload or header will output only the payload or only the warc http header if any respectively warcio is licensed under the apache license and is part of the webrecorder project see notice and license for detail

basic and advanced example the example within each service assume that you already have service credential if you run your app in ibm cloud the sdk get credential from the vcap service http console bluemix net doc service watson getting started variable html environment variable watson service are migrating to token based identity and access management iam authentication with some service instance you authenticate to the api by using iam iam in other instance you authenticate by providing the username and password username and password for the service instance note authenticating with the x watson authorization token header is deprecated the token continues to work with cloud foundry service but is not supported for service that use identity and access management iam authentication see here for detail to find out which authentication to use view the service credential you find the service credential for authentication the same way for all watson service go to the ibm cloud dashboard page either click an existing watson service instance in your resource list or click create resource ai and create a service instance click on the manage item in the left nav bar of your service instance on this page you should be able to see your credential for accessing your service instance there are two way to supply the credential you found above to the sdk for authentication with a credential file you just need to put the file in the right place and the sdk will do the work of parsing and authenticating you can get this file by clicking the download button for the credential in the manage tab of your service instance the file downloaded will be called ibm credential env this is the name the sdk will search for and must be preserved unless you want to configure the file path more on that later the sdk will look for your ibm credential env file in the following place in order your system s home directorythe top level directory of the project you re using the sdk inas long a you set that up correctly you don t have to worry about setting any authentication option in your code so for example if you created and downloaded the credential file for your discovery instance you just need to do the following and that s it if you re using more than one service at a time in your code and get two different ibm credential env file just put the content together in one ibm credential env file and the sdk will handle assigning credential to their appropriate service if you would like to configure the location name of your credential file you can set an environment variable called ibm credential file this will take precedence over the location specified above here s how you can do that where path is something like home user downloads file name env if you d prefer to set authentication value manually in your code the sdk support that a well the way you ll do this depends on what type of credential your service instance give you ibm cloud is migrating to token based identity and access management iam authentication iam authentication us a service api key to get an access token that is passed with the call access token are valid for approximately one hour and must be regenerated you supply either an iam service api key or an access token use the api key to have the sdk manage the lifecycle of the access token the sdk request an access token ensures that the access token is valid and refreshes it if necessary use the access token if you want to manage the lifecycle yourself for detail see authenticating with iam token tested image fit in memory the data and xarray data property will load the whole scene into memory the get image data function will load the whole scene into memory and then retrieve the specified chunk if your image doesn t fit in memory the dask data and xarray dask data property and the get image dask data function will not load any piece of the imaging data into memory until you specifically call compute on the returned dask array in doing so you will only then load the selected chunk in memory read stitched data or single tile a a dimension reader that support mosaic tile stitching if the file format reader support stitching mosaic tile together the aicsimage object will default to stitching the tile back together this behavior can be manually turned off if the reader doe not support stitching tile together the m tile index will be available on the aicsimage object if the file format reader detects mosaic tile in the image the reader object will store the tile a a dimension if tile stitching is implemented the reader can also return the stitched image there are function available on both the aicsimage and reader object to help with single tile positioning if aicsimageio find coordinate information for the spatial temporal dimension of the image in metadata you can use xarray for indexing by coordinate see xarray indexing and selecting data documentation for more information file system specification fsspec allows for common object storage service s gc etc to act like normal filesystems by following the same base specification across them all aicsimageio utilizes this standard specification to make it possible to read directly from remote resource when the specification is installed remote reading requires that the file system specification grain customization of the metadata scene or if you want to save an array a an ome tiff the writer class can also be used to customize a needed see ometiffwriter documentation for more detail in most case aicsimage save is usually a good default but there are other image writer available for more information please refer to our writer documentation aicsimageio is benchmarked using asv you can find the benchmark result for every commit to main starting at the release on our benchmark page see our developer resource for information related to developing the code if you find aicsimageio useful
