description: a tracing profiler that is multithreading asyncio and gevent aware cpython standard distribution come with three deterministic profilers cprofile profile and hotshot cprofile is implemented a a c module based on lsprof profile is in pure python and hotshot can be seen a a small subset of a cprofile the major issue is that all of these profilers lack support for multi threaded program and cpu time if you want to profile a multi threaded application you must give an entry point to these profilers and then maybe merge the output none of these profilers are designed to work on long running multi threaded application it is also not possible to profile an application that start stop retrieve trace on the fly with these profilers now fast forwarding to with the latest improvement on asyncio library and asynchronous framework most of the current profilers lack the ability to show correct wall cpu time or even call count information per coroutine thus we need a different kind of approach to profile asynchronous code yappi with v introduces the concept of coroutine profiling with coroutine profiling you should be able to profile correct wall cpu time and call count of your coroutine including the time spent in context switch too you can see detail here can be installed via pypior from the source directly you can profile a multithreaded application via yappi and can easily retrieve per thread profile information by filtering on ctx id with get func stats api you can use filter callback on get func stats api to filter on function module or whatever available in yfuncstat object you can see that coroutine wall time s are correctly profiled you can use yappi to profile greenlet application now introductionclock typesapicoroutine profiling new in greenlet profiling new in note yes i know i should be moving doc to readthedocs io stay tuned special thanks to a jesse jiryu davis yappi is the default profiler in pycharm if you have yappi installed pycharm will use it see the official documentation for more detail

description: this package is implementation of improving spherical k mean for document clustering fast initialization sparse centroid projection and efficient cluster labeling kim et al cosine is more effective than euclidean when measuring the distance between two high dimensional or sometimes sparse document vector however scikit learn k mean package provides only euclidean based k mean additionally labeling cluster can be very helpful for interpreting the clustering result spherical k mean work well both with sparse vector representation such a bag of word model or distributed representation such a doc vec or other document embedding method in lower dimensional vector space silhouette score method is useful to define the number of cluster k however silhouette score method doe not work well in a high dimensional vector space such a bag of word and doc vec model space one of the heuristic method to define the number of cluster is to train k mean with large k first and subsequently merge similar one this method is also useful for preventing the uniform effect which cause the size of all cluster to be similar soyclustering provides spherical k mean k mean which us cosine distance a a distance metric and keyword extraction based clustering labeling function furthermore the function for visualizing pairwise distance between centroid will help you to check whether redundant cluster exist allowing you to remove redundant cluster by merging them soyclustering also provides a fast initialization method that is effective in a high dimensional vector space when the size of the input data is large the initialization method set k to be the below table decsribes relative speed up of proposed initialization method with alpha compared to kmeans x time faster you can read a matrix market file a follows note that the file must include tokenized output although the spherical k mean function can be used for input in distributed representation such a doc vec our cluster labeling algorithm work only for bag of word model sperical k mean can be used a follows init similar cut indicates our initializer that is effective in a high dimensional vector space if you want to preserve the sparsity of the centroid vector you can set minimum df factor other interface are similar to those of scikit learn k mean function with fit predict you can retrieve the label from the clustering result when the verbose mode is set computation speed and the level of sparsity during the initizalition and each iteration is printed cluster labeling can be used to intrepret the clustering result the proportion keywords function of soyclustering us a keyword extraction based method to return keywords describing each cluster for it input argument you need to provide cluster centroid vector a list of vocabulary a str and label the table in below is the result of cluster label from a trained k mean with k and m document setting a large k lead to redundant cluster you can identify these redundant cluster by carefully examining the pairwise distance between the cluster if you find redundant cluster you can easily merge them into a single cluster after merging you can check the size of dark square in the diagonal entry of the pairwise distance matrix if the redundant cluster are indeed successfully merged the number of dark sqaures in the diagonal entry should have been reduced the function merge close cluster group similar cluster in which the distance between them is smaller than max dist the centroid of the new cluster is a weighted average of original centroid vector from the variable group you can return the cluster index prior and after merging in addition the repository kmeans to pyldavis provides k mean visualization using pyldavis

description: the advanced scientific data format asdf is a next generation interchange format for scientific data this package contains the python implementation of the asdf standard more information on the asdf standard itself can be found here the asdf format ha the following feature a hierarchical human readable metadata format implemented using yaml numerical array are stored a binary data block which can be memory mapped data block can optionally be compressed the structure of the data can be automatically validated using schema implemented using json schema native python data type numerical type string dicts list are serialized automaticallyasdf can be extended to serialize custom data typesasdf is under active development on github more information on contributing can be found below this section outline basic use case of the asdf package for creating and reading asdf file we re going to store several numpy array and other data to an asdf file we do this by creating a tree which is simply a dict and we provide it a input to the constructor of asdffile if we open the newly created file s metadata section we can see some of the key feature of asdf on display the metadata in the file mirror the structure of the tree that wa stored it is hierarchical and human readable notice that metadata ha been added to the tree that wa not explicitly given by the user notice also that the numerical array data is not stored in the metadata tree itself instead it is stored a binary data block below the metadata section not shown above it is possible to compress the array data when writing the file the built in compression algorithm are zlib and bzp the lz algorithm becomes available when the lz package is installed other compression algorithm may be available via extension to read an existing asdf file we simply use the top level open function of the asdf package the open function also work a a context handler to get a quick overview of the data stored in the file use the top level asdffile info method the asdffile behaves like a python dict and node are accessed like any other dictionary entry array data remains unloaded until it is explicitly accessed by default uncompressed data block are memory mapped for efficient access memory mapping can be disabled by using the copy array option of open when reading for more information and for advanced usage example see the documentation out of the box the asdf package automatically serializes and deserializes native python type it is possible to extend asdf by implementing custom tag that correspond to custom user type more information on extending asdf can be found in the official documentation stable release of the asdf python package are registered at pypi the latest stable version can be installed using pip the latest development version of asdf is available from the master branch on github to clone the project to install to install in development mode to install the test dependency from a source checkout of the repository to run the unit test from a source checkout of the repository it is also possible to run the test suite from an installed version of the package it is also possible to run the test using tox to list all available environment to run a specific environment more detailed documentation on this software package can be found here more information on the asdf standard itself can be found here there are two mailing list for asdf asdf usersasdf developersif you are looking for the adaptable seismic data format information can be found here we welcome feedback and contribution to the project contribution of code documentation or general feedback are all appreciated please follow the contributing guideline to submit an issue or a pull request we strive to provide a welcoming community to all of our user by abiding to the code of conduct

description: the parsing module implement an lr parser generator a well a the runtime support for using a generated parser via the lr and glr parser driver there is no special parser generator input file format but the parser generator still need to know what class method correspond to various aspect of the parser this information is specified via docstrings which the parser generator introspects in order to generate a parser only one parser specification can be embedded in each module but it is possible to share module between parser specification so that for example the same token definition can be used by multiple parser specification the parsing table are lr but they are generated using a fast algorithm that avoids creating duplicate state that result when using the generic lr algorithm creation time and table size are on par with the lalr algorithm however lalr can create reduce reduce conflict that don t exist in a true lr parser for more information on the algorithm see parsing table generation requires non trivial amount of time for large grammar however it is still quite fast internal pickling support make it possible to cache the most recent version of the parsing table on disk and use the table if the current parser specification is still compatible with the one that wa used to generate the pickled parsing table since the compatibility checking is quite fast even for large grammar this remove the need to use the standard code generation method that is used by most parser generator parser specification are encapsulated by the spec class parser instance use spec instance but are themselves based on separate class this allows multiple parser instance to exist simultaneously without requiring multiple copy of the parsing table there are two separate parser driver class standard characteristic finite state machine cfsm driver based on unambiguous lr parsing table this driver is faster than the glr driver but it cannot deal with all parsing table that the glr driver can generalized lr driver capable of tracking multiple parse tree simultaneously if the split precedence is used to mark ambiguous action this driver is closely based on elkhound s design which is described in a technical report parser generator directive are embedded in docstrings and must begin with a character followed immediately by one of several keywords fail nonassoc left right split token start nonterm reduceall of these directive are associated with class except for reduce reduce is associated with method within non terminal class the parsing module provides base class from which precedence token and non terminal must be derived this is not a restrictive a it sound since there is nothing preventing for example a master token class that subclass parsing token which all of the actual token type then subclass also nothing prevents using multiple inheritance folowing are the base class to be subclassed by parser specification precedencetokennontermthe parsing module implement the following exception class specerror when there is a problem with the grammar specificationparsingexception any problem that occurs during parsingunexpectedtoken when the input sequence contains a token that is not allowed by the grammar including end of input in order to maintain compatibility with legacy code the parsing module defines the following alias new code should use the exception above that do not shadow python s builtin exception exception superclass for all exception that can be raisedsyntaxerror alias for unexpectedtokenattributeerrorauthor jason evans jasone canonware comgithub repo http github com magicstack parsing

description: jsonfield is a reusable model field that allows you to store validated json automatically handling serialization to and from the database to use add jsonfield jsonfield to one of your model note django contrib postgres now support postgresql s jsonb type which includes extended querying capability if you re an end user of postgresql and want full featured json support then it is recommended that you use the built in jsonfield however jsonfield is still useful when your app need to be database agnostic or when the built in jsonfield s extended querying is not being leveraged e g a configuration field jsonfield aim to support all current version of django however the explicity tested version are python django a stated above jsonfield is not intended to provide extended querying capability that said you may perform the same basic lookup provided by regular text field e g exact or regex lookup since value are stored a serialized json it is highly recommended that you test your query to ensure the expected result are returned a model field s null argument typically control whether null value may be stored in it column by setting a not null constraint however because jsonfield serializes it value including null this option instead control how null value are persisted if null true then null are not serialized and are stored a a null value in the database if null false then the null is instead stored in it serialized form this in turn affect how null value may be queried both field support exact matching however if you want to use the isnull lookup you must set null true note that a jsonfield null doe not prevent null from being stored achieving this must instead be handled with a validator by default python deserializes json into dict object this behavior differs from the standard json behavior because python dicts do not have ordered key to overcome this limitation and keep the sort order of ordereddict key the deserialisation can be adjusted on model initialisation jsonfield jsoncharfieldsubclasses model charfield instead of model textfield the test suite requires tox then run the tox command which will run all test job or to test just description: soundcard is a library for playing and recording audio without resorting to a cpython extension instead it is implemented using the wonderful cffi and the native audio library of linux window and macos soundcard is cross platform and support linux pulseaudio mac coreaudio and window wasapi while the programming interface is identical across platform sound card naming scheme and default block size can vary between device and platform soundcard is still in development all major feature work on all platform but there are a few known issue that still need to be fixed if you find a bug please open an issue and i will try to fix it or open a pull request and i will try to include your fix into soundcard however please be aware that this is a hobby project of mine that i am developing for free and in my spare time while i try to be a accomodating a possible i can not guarantee a timely response to issue publishing open source software on github doe not imply an obligation to fix your problem right now please be civil here is how you get to your speaker and microphone all of these function return speaker and microphone object which can be used for playback and recording all data passed in and out of these object are frame channel numpy array by default soundcard record and play at the operating system s default configuration particularly on laptop this configuration might have extreme latency up to multiple second in order to request lower latency pas a blocksize to player or recorder this tell the operating system your desired latency and it will try to honor your request a best it can on window wasapi setting exclusive mode true might help too this is currently experimental another source of latency is in the record function which buffer output up to the requested numframes in general for optimal latency you should use a numframes significantly lower than the blocksize above maybe by a factor of two or four to get the audio data a quickly a absolutely possible you can use numframes none which will return whatever audio data is available right now without any buffering note that this might receive different number of frame each time with the above setting block size of sample or ten millisecond are usually no problem the total latency of playback and recording is dependent on how these buffer are handled by the operating system though and might be significantly higher additionally it might help to experiment with advice from here http askubuntu com question how can i fix choppy audio and edit your etc pulse default pa file to replace the line sayingwithand then do not forget to restart pulseaudio withsome professional sound card have large number of channel if you want to record or play only a subset of those channel you can specify a channel map for playback a channel map of will play three channel audio data on the physical channel one four and five for recording a channel map of will return three channel audio data recorded from the physical channel one four and five in addition pulseaudio linux defines channel a the mono mix of all channel for both playback and recording coreaudio macos defines channel a silence for both playback and recording q how to make it work on a headless raspberry pi a pulseaudio is not installed by default on the raspberry pi o lite distribution http www raspberrypi org software operating system in order to use soundcard you have to install pulseaudio first and edit the configuration with a fix to avoid the main output to be in mono only window wasapi currently record garbage if you record only a single channel the reason for this is yet unknown multi channel and channel map work though window wasapi silently ignores the blocksize in some case apparently it only support variable block size in exclusive mode error message often report some internal cffi backend error this will be improved in the future implement fixed block size when recording thank you pariente manuel add a test suite and various fix for window various fix for macos add latency property to linux pulseaudio thank you pariente manuel add loopback support for window thank you jan leskovec add bug fix for ipython on window thank you sebastian michel add sphinx readthedocs documentation add support for python thank you daniel r kumor add experimental support for exclusive mode on window fix sample rate conversion on macos fix silence recording on macos fix exception when monitoring default device on linux thank you inti pelupessy fix crash when opening many stream on linux fix attribute error when accessing stream state on linux thank you dav sindri p tursson fix inconsistent dtypes when recording on linux fix silent recording on window get and set the pulseaudio program name on linux thank you philipp a fix error with unicode soundcard name on window thank you bakezq add support for pyinstaller v thank you bob thomas add compatibility with window thank you demberto add compatibility with nixos library naming thank you shithead fix deprecation for python thank you nekyo fix deprecation in recent numpy

description: this is a python port of google s libphonenumber library it support python and python x in the same codebase with no to conversion needed original java code is copyright c the libphonenumber author release history derived from upstream release note install using pip with the main object that the library deal with is a phonenumber object you can create this from a string representing a phone number using the parse function but you also need to specify the country that the phone number is being dialled from unless the number is in e format which is globally unique the phonenumber object that parse produce typically still need to be validated to check whether it s a possible number e g it ha the right number of digit or a valid number e g it s in an assigned exchange the parse function will also fail completely with a numberparseexception on input that cannot be uniquely parsed or that can t possibly be phone number once you ve got a phone number a common task is to format it in a standardized format there are a few format available under phonenumberformat and the format number function doe the formatting if your application ha a ui that allows the user to type in a phone number it s nice to get the formatting applied a the user type the asyoutypeformatter object allows this sometimes you ve got a larger block of text that may or may not have some phone number inside it for this the phonenumbermatcher object provides the relevant functionality you can iterate over it to retrieve a sequence of phonenumbermatch object each of these match object hold a phonenumber object together with information about where the match occurred in the original string you might want to get some information about the location that corresponds to a phone number the geocoder area description for number doe this when possible for mobile number in some country you can also find out information about which carrier originally owned a phone number you might also be able to retrieve a list of time zone name that the number potentially belongs to for more information about the other functionality available from the library look in the unit test or in the original libphonenumber project the library includes a lot of metadata potentially giving a significant memory overhead there are two mechanism for dealing with this the phonenumberslite version of the library doe not include the geocoder carrier and timezone package which can be useful if you have problem installing the main phonenumbers library due to space memory limitation if you need to ensure that the metadata memory use is accounted for at start of day i e that a subsequent on demand load of metadata will not cause a pause or memory exhaustion the phonenumberslite version of the package doe not include the geocoding carrier and timezone metadata which can be useful if you have problem installing the main phonenumbers package due to space memory limitation the library includes a set of type stub file to support static type checking by library user these stub file signal the type that should be used and may also be of use in ides which have integrated type checking functionality these file are written for python and a such type checking the library with these stub on python is unsupported

description: moderngl is a python wrapper over opengl core that simplifies the creation of simple graphic application like scientific simulation game or user interface usually acquiring in depth knowledge of opengl requires a steep learning curve in contrast moderngl is easy to learn and use moreover it is capable of rendering with high performance and quality with le code written the majority of the moderngl code base is also written in c for high performance note from moderngl context creation is delegated to the glcontext package this make u able to expand and improve context creation without releasing new version of moderngl it also make it possible for user to customize their own context creation and the bar for contributing should be lower new backends can be created using ctypes or c for complete example please visit the example with pyopengl using the original opengl api you have to write three line to achieve a simple task like binding a vbo with moderngl you need just one simple line per vbo to achieve the same result in many case yes the core function of moderngl are written in c opengl function are called in quick succession so these call together count a a single python function call most of the call only require opengl but subroutine and compute shaders require opengl and opengl opengl came out in february with up to date driver you will be able to description: confugue is a hierarchical configuration framework for python it provides a wrapper class for nested configuration dictionary usually loaded from yaml file which can be used to easily configure complicated object hierarchy the package is ideal for configuring deep learning experiment these often have large number of hyperparameters and managing all their value globally can quickly get tedious instead confugue allows each part of the deep learning model to be automatically supplied with hyperparameters from a yaml configuration file eliminating the need to pas them around the nested structure of the configuration file follows the hierarchy of the model architecture with each part of the model having access to the corresponding section of the file a an example here is a simplified code snippet from a deep learning project which us confugue the model could then be configured using the following config file overriding the value specified in the code and filling in the one that are missing the package is available from pypi and can be installed with pip install confugue the doc include quick start guide for deep learning user available a a colab notebookgeneral guide for python usersapi referenceconfugue is somewhat similar to gin but is much more minimalistic yet in some way more powerful some advantage of confugue over gin are it is straightforward to configure many object of the same type with different parameter for each with gin this is possible but it requires using scope any function or class can be configured without having been explicitly registered config file may override the type of an object or the function being called while preserving the default parameter provided by the caller it is possible to access and even manipulate configuration value explicitly instead of or in addition to having them supplied a parameter the structure of the config file is nested typically following the call hierarchy compared to gin s linear structure on the other hand confugue doesn t have some of the advanced feature of gin such a config file inclusion or operative configuration logging it also doesn t support macro but a similar effect can be achieved using pyyaml s alias some other difference which may be viewed a advantage or disadvantage in different situation are gin config file specify default value for function parameter which can be overridden by the caller in confugue on the other hand the config file ha the final say gin will seamlessly load default from the configuration file every time a configurable function or class is called confugue is more explicit in that the caller first ha to ask for a specific key from the configuration file sacred also offer configuration functionality but it goal are much broader focusing on experiment management including keeping track of metric and other information confugue on the other hand is not specifically targeted to scientific experimentation even though it is particularly well suited for machine learning experiment a for the configuration mechanism itself sacred ha so called captured function which resemble configurable function in confugue or gin but doe not offer the same ability to configure arbitrary object in a hierarchical way

description: a python reader writer of ri reference file parsing a file path can also be used to read ri file if an encoding is not specified in load the default system encoding will be used writing the most field contain string value but some like first author a are parsed into list the default mapping were created from specification scattered around the web but to our knowledge there is not one single source of ri truth so these may need to be modified for specific export system wikipediaresearcheridrefmanrefman ri format zoterothe parser use a tag key mapping which one can override by calling rispy load with the mapping parameter list tag can be customized in the same way by passing a list to the list tag parameter there are a few flag that can be passed to rispy load and rispy dump that change how rispy deal with tag for example setting skip unknown tag to true will cause rispy do not read or write tag not in the tag map more can be found in the docstrings for each class if more customization is necessary a custom implementation can be created see next section not all ri file follow the same formatting guideline there is an interface for creating custom implementation for reading and writing such file an implementation contains the method and parameter used to work with ri file and should be passed to rispy load or rispy dump creating a custom implentation involves creating a class that inherits a base class and overriding the necessary variable and method one of the existing parser can also be inherited inheriting an existing class is advantageous if only minor change need to be made the section below document what is available to be overriden along with a few example custom parser can inherit risparser the default parser or baseparser various parameter and method can be overridden when creating a new parser these are documented in the baseparser docstring example writing is very similar to parsing a custom writer class can inherit basewriter or one if it subclass such a riswriter example other various utility included in rispy are documented below a method is available to convert common ri reference type into more readable term it take a list of reference and return a copy of that list with modified reference type the map for this conversion is located in config py some ri like format contain rich citation data for example list and nested attribute that rispy doe not support software specializing on these format include nbib par the pubmed or medline formatcommon developer command are in the provided makefile if you don t have make installed you can view the make command and run the command from the command line manually github action are currently enabled to run lint and test when submitting a pull request

description: hyper parameter optimization extension for asreview it us the hyperopt package to quickly optimize parameter of the different model the hyper parameter and their sample space are defined in the asreview package and automatically used for hyper parameter optimization the easiest way to install the hyper parameter optimization package is to use the command line after installation of the visualization package asreview should automatically detect it test this by it should list three new entry point hyper active hyper passive and hyper cluster the three entry point are used in a roughly similar fashion the main difference between them is the type of model that have to be supplied to get help for entry point type which result in the following option the extension will by default search for datasets in the data directory relative to the current working directory either put your datasets there or specify and data directory the output of the run will by default be stored in the output directory relative to the current path an example of a structure that ha been created the file with name trial pkl are special file that contain data on which trial were run to list these trial use the following command it should give a list of trial sorted by the loss lower is better the column name apart from the loss are prefixed with the kind of parameter it is the default number of iteration is which you ll probably want to increase it depends on the number of hyper parameter that need to be optimized but several hundred iteration is probably a good estimate for most combination to get reasonably close to the optimum in all case use good common sense if the loss is still going down at a quick pace do a few more iteration the hyperopt extension ha built in support for mpi mpi is used for parallelization of run on a local pc with an mpi implementation like openmpi installed one could run with core if you want to be slightly more efficient on a machine with a low number of core you can run job on the mpi server a well on super computer one should sometimes replace mpirun with srun

together with a set of unordered pair of these vertex for an undirected graph or a set of ordered pair for a directed graph these pair are known a edge arc or line for an undirected graph and a arrow directed edge directed arc or directed line for a directed graph the vertex may be part of the graph structure or may be external entity represented by integer index or reference the graph class allows you to create node and edge and visualize the resulting graph edge can have direction which indicates parent child relationship to construct a new graph use graph the add node method creates a description: a simple implementation of subcommands for docopt docopt subcommands allows you to create subcommand based program using docopt a subcommand based program is one in which the main program us a subcommand argument to tell it what to do the classic example of such a program is git the git command with no argument doesn t do much of anything instead it s the first argument to git the subcommand that tell it what to actually do for example will give you the log for your repository likewise is the subcommand for rebasing docopt subcommands is here to help you create similar kind of command line tool with docopt the basic idea behind docopt subcommands is simple then docopt subcommands doe the work of stitching everything together into a subcommand driven program here s how it look from the included exampels basic example py if you run this program at the command line you ll see that you have a nice subcommand based cli program for more example see the example directory many subcommand based program have a set of option that are common to all command a common example is verbose which cause the program to print more information not matter which command is executed with docopt subcommands you specify these common option in the top level docstring like this top level doc program usage program option command args option h help show this screen verbose use verbose outputavailable command available command with this docstring you can provide the verbose flag for any subcommand critically common option must be provided before the subcommand name so if bar wa a subcommand in your program you would write my program verbose barbut not my program bar verbosedocopt subcommands par the complete command line in two pass the first pas par it with the top level docstring while the second pas us the docstring for the specific command and only par the part of the command line after the common option it then provides both of the parsed dicts to the subcommand handler the first argument to the handler is the result of the first pas and the second argument is the result of the second pas with this system you can then use a single set of code to do common description: read write lock for asyncio a rwlock maintains a pair of associated lock one for read only operation and one for writing the read lock may be held simultaneously by multiple reader task so long a there are no writer the write lock is exclusive whether or not a read write lock will improve performance over the use of a mutual exclusion lock depends on the frequency that the data is read compared to being modified for example a collection that is initially populated with data and thereafter infrequently modified while being frequently searched is an ideal candidate for the use of a read write lock however if update become frequent then the data spends most of it time being exclusively locked and there is little if any increase in concurrency implementation is almost direct port from this patch requires python by default rwlock switch context on lock acquiring that allows to other waiting task get the lock even if task that hold the lock doesn t contain context switch await fut statement the default behavior can be switched off by fast argument rwlock fast true long story short lock is safe by default but if you sure you have context switch await async with async for or yield from statement inside locked code you may want to use fast true for minor speedup tla specification of aiorwlock provided in this repository aiorwlock is offered under the apache license loop usage in asyncio sleep call make the library forward compatible with python fix a bug with cancelation during acquire thanks romasku deprecate passing explicit loop argument to rwlock constructordeprecate creation of rwlock instance outside of async function contextminimal supported version is python the library work with python and python seamlesslywake up all reader after writer release lock thanks ranyixu fixed python compatibilityremoved old yield from syntaxminimal supported version is python removed support for none async context managersfix corner case and deadlock when description: a library for creating columnar output string using data a input or for that fresh docker look note that when using the no border argument the header will be capitalized by default this can be disabled by passing preformatted header true columnar also support emojis and character that take up two display column assuming your display know what to do with them columnar support pattern which are two item tuples each containing a regular expression and a function the regular expression is applied to each item in data using re match and if there is a match the corresponding function is applied to the text of that element only the first matching pattern is applied meaning pattern can be prioritized by their order in the input array this can be used to perform colorization casing or other custom task that will affect the display of the text in the table a noted above color may be applied to text by adding it to the text through a pattern however text may also be pre colored by applying ansi color code to the text before it is passed to columnar a made easy by library like click and colorama note however that any color that is applied will be applied to the content of the whole cell for example if the text for a cell isthe entire cell s text will be turned blue if your table ha a large number of column or you wish to highlight a subset of the column use the select keyword argument it take a list of string which are compiled to regular expression using re compile arg re i and used to select column using pattern search column name for example given the following columnsusing select name code will select all column except the birthdate column it is often the case that one or more column of the data will not be useful for example column where all the value are null or to filter out these column use the drop keyword argument this argument take a list of value and drop any column whose content are a subset of those value for example given four columnsusing drop null na none will drop the second and fourth column even though the first column contains a dash also there are an infinite number of way to determine column sizing and text wrapping given a dataset this package allows the user to specify a minimum column width a maximum column width and a wrap max which partially define wrapping and column sizing the rest of the logic that go into determining how to fit data into a table when the data is wider than the terminal employ a pretty simple heuristic first determine how wide each column want to be without wrapping if all the column are too wide to fit on the screen shrink a many column a are needed in order for the table to fit starting with the widest column and progressing through the column from largest to smallest if the size of the column fall below the minimum column width then raise an exception specifically a columnar exception tableoverflowerror this should only happen if there are so many column that terminal width num column is le than the minimum column width the content of a column are wrapped a needed to fit in the column with no effort made to split on space however new line character are preserved and tab character are replaced with four space the maximum number of time the content of a column are wrapped before being truncated is given by wrap max another way to think about wrap max is that wrap max is the maximum number of row a single cell can occupy any content past the wrap max th row is truncated an iterable of iterables typically a list of list of string where each string will occupy it own cell in the table however list element need not be string no matter what is passed each element in the list is converted to a string using str a list of string one for each column in data which will be displayed a the table header if left a none this will produce a table that doe not have a header row a explained above pattern accepts a list of two item tuples which can be used to transform the input data in order to perform task like text coloring capitalization or other formatting a explained above drop take a list of string and if any column contains only element in that list the column and it corresponding header will be excluded from the table can be used to exclude column where all the value are null or etc if an empty list is passed default then no column are dropped accepts a list of string that are compiled to regular expression using the case insensitive re i flag any column that match any of these regular expression is kept while all other column are dropped if select is specified drop is ignored meaning that it is possible to display column that may have been dropped by drop by specifying them in select passing an empty list default cause all column not dropped by drop to be displayed accepts a boolean value that specifies whether or not to display the border between row and column passing true will hide all the border and convert the header to all cap for a more minimalistic look similar to the unix bash command display only head number of row of data for examplewill display the first four row of data passing default will display all the data specifies how each column should be justified justification option are either l c or r for left center and right justification respectively this argument accepts either a single value or a list with len list num column if a single value is specified the justification for all column will be set to that value otherwise if a list is supplied value will be applied to each column individually for exmaplewill center all three column whilewill right justify column one center column two and left justify column three set the maximum number of time a line will wrap inside it cell another way to think of this is that wrap max is the maximum number of line that a cell can occupy new line character in the input are preserved meaning that they count against the value of wrap max set the maximum width for a column causing the content to wrap if they contain more character than max column width setting this value to none default will only cause text to be wrapped if the whole table is too wide to fit on the screen causing the column sizing algorithm to kick in set the minimum width of a column adding whitespace to either the left side right side or both side depending on the value of justify note that if min column width is too high the table may not fit on the screen and a columnar exception tableoverflowerror will be thrown specifies the character or string used to draw border between the row specifies the character or string used to draw border between the column specifies the width of the output display if left a none the width will default to shutil get terminal size column however for case where the default doe not give a desirable result the display width can be specified here control header formatting when no border true the default false will cause the header to be automatically capitalized true will use the header a provided without any modification

description: the aim of this project is to provide a robust cross platform and cross version implementation of the processpoolexecutor class of concurrent future it notably feature consistent and robust spawn behavior all process are started using fork exec on posix system this ensures safer interaction with third party library on the contrary multiprocessing pool us fork without exec by default causing third party runtimes to crash e g openmp macos accelerate reusable executor strategy to avoid re spawning a complete executor every time a singleton executor instance can be reused and dynamically resized if necessary across consecutive call to limit spawning and shutdown overhead the worker process can be shutdown automatically after a configurable idling timeout to free system resource transparent cloudpickle integration to call interactively defined function and lambda expression in parallel it is also possible to register a custom pickler implementation to handle inter process communication no need for if name main in script thanks to the use of cloudpickle to call function defined in the main module it is not required to protect the code calling parallel function under window deadlock free implementation one of the major concern in standard multiprocessing and concurrent future module is the ability of the pool executor to handle crash of worker process this library intends to fix those possible deadlock and send back meaningful error note that the implementation of concurrent future processpoolexecutor that come with python is a robust a the executor from loky but the latter also work for older version of python the recommended way to install loky is with pip loky can also be installed from source usingnote that loky ha an optional dependency on psutil to allow early memory leak detection the basic usage of loky relies on the get reusable executor which internally manages a custom processpoolexecutor object which is reused or re spawned depending on the context for more advance usage see our documentationto contribute to loky first create an account on github once this is done fork the loky repository to have your own repository clone it using git clone on the computer where you want to work make your change in your clone push them to your github account test them on several computer and when you are happy with them send a pull request to the main repository to run the test suite you need the pytest version and psutil module from the root of the project run the test suite using while developping loky we had some bad experience trying to debug deadlock when using multiprocessing pool and concurrent future processpoolexecutor especially when calling function with non picklable argument or returned value at the beginning of the project when we had to chose a name we had dealt with so many deadlock that we wanted some kind of invocation to repel them hence loky a mix of a god lock and the y that make it somehow cooler and nicer and also le likely to result in name conflict in google result fix to avoid those deadlock in concurrent future were also contributed upstream in python a a le mystical way to repel the deadlock dthis work is supported by the center for data science funded by the idex paris saclay anr idex

description: read and write sa transport file xpt sa us a handful of archaic file format xport xpt cport sa bdat if someone publishes their data in one of those format this python package will help you convert the data into a more useful format if someone like the fda asks you for an xpt file this package can write it for you xport is the binary file format used by a bunch of united state government agency for publishing data set it made a lot of sense if you were trying to read data file on your ibm mainframe back in the official sa specification for xport is relatively straightforward the hardest part is converting ibm format floating point to ieee format which the specification explains in detail there wa an update to the xpt specification for sa v and above this module ha not yet been updated to work with the new version however if you re using sa v you re probably not using xpt format the change to the format appear to be trivial change to the metadata but this module s current error checking will raise a valueerror if you d like an update for v please let me know by submitting an issue this project requires python v grab the latest stable version from pypi this module follows the common pattern of providing load and load function for reading data from a sa file format the xpt decoder xport load and xport load return a xport library which is a mapping dict like of xport dataset s the xport dataset is a subclass of panda dataframe with sa metadata attribute name label etc the column of a xport dataset are xport variable type which are subclass of panda series with sa metadata name label format etc if you re not familiar with panda s dataframes it s easy to think of them a a dictionary of column mapping variable name to variable data the sa transport xport format only support two kind of data each value is either numeric or character so xport load decodes the value a either str or float note that since xpt file are in an unusual binary format you should open them using mode rb you can also use the xport module a a command line tool to convert an xpt file to csv comma separated value file the xport executable is a friendly alias for python m xport caution if this command line doe not work with the lastest version it should be working with version to get this version we can either download the file from this link or simply type the following command line your bash terminal pip install xport the xport package follows the common pattern of providing dump and dump function for writing data to a sa file format because the xport dataset is an extension of panda dataframe you can create datasets in a variety of way converting easily from a dataframe to a dataset sa transport v restricts variable name to character with a strange preference for uppercase and label to character if you want the relative comfort of sa transport v s limit of character please make an enhancement request it s likely that most people will be using panda dataframes for the bulk of their analysis work and will want to convert to xpt at the very end of their process i m happy to fix bug improve the interface or make the module faster just submit an issue and i ll take a look if you work for a corporation or well funded non profit please consider a sponsorship current and past sponsor include this project is configured to be developed in a conda environment original version by jack cushman major revision by michael selik and minor revision by alfred chan minor revision by derek croote initial release major revision add numpy and panda converter revise api to the pattern of from to format reader yield regular tuples not namedtuplesrevise api to the load dump pattern enable specifying dataset name variable name label and format allow dump dataframe instead of requiring a dataset fix a bug that incorrectly display a dash when it s a null for numeric field enable reading transport version file merry christmas add support for special missing value like a that extend float enable writing transport version file happy new year fix issue with writing dataset label and variable label add beta support for changing the text encoding for data and metadata fix issue with v format when the dataset ha no long label

description: smart open is a python library for efficient streaming of very large file from to storage such a s gc azure blob storage hdfs webhdfs http http sftp or local filesystem it support transparent on the fly de compression for a variety of different format smart open is a drop in replacement for python s built in open it can do anything open can compatible fall back to native open wherever possible plus lot of nifty extra stuff on top python is no longer supported if you need python please use smart open the last version to support python working with large remote file for example using amazon s boto python library is a pain boto s object upload fileobj and object download fileobj method require gotcha prone boilerplate to use successfully such a constructing file like object wrapper smart open shield you from that it build on boto and other remote storage library but offer a clean unified pythonic api the result is le code for you to write and fewer bug to make smart open is well tested well documented and ha a simple pythonic api other example of url that smart open accepts smart open support a wide range of storage solution including aws s google cloud and azure each individual solution ha it own dependency by default smart open doe not install any dependency in order to keep the installation size small you can install these dependency explicitly using or if you don t mind installing a large number of third party library you can install all dependency using be warned that this option increase the installation size significantly e g over mb if you re upgrading from smart open version x and below please check out the migration guide for detailed api info see the online help or click here to view the help in your browser for the sake of simplicity the example below assume you have all the dependency installed i e you have done the top level compression parameter control compression decompression behavior when reading and writing the supported value for this parameter are infer from extension default behavior disable gz bz by default smart open determines the compression algorithm to use based on the file extension you can override this behavior to either disable compression or explicitly specify the algorithm to use to disable compression to specify the algorithm explicitly e g for non standard file extension you can also easily add support for other file extension and compression format for example to open xz compressed file lzma is in the standard library in python and greater for use backports lzma smart open support a wide range of transport option out of the box including s http http read only ssh scp and sftpwebhdfsgcsazure blob storageeach option involves setting up it own set of parameter for example for accessing s you often need to set up authentication like api key or a profile name smart open s open function accepts a keyword argument transport params which accepts additional parameter for the transport layer here are some example of using this parameter for the full list of keyword argument supported by each transport option see the documentation smart open us the boto library to talk to s boto ha several mechanism for determining the credential to use by default smart open will defer to boto and let the latter take care of the credential there are several way to override this behavior the first is to pas a boto client object a a transport parameter to the open function you can customize the credential when constructing the session for the client smart open will then use the session when talking to s your second option is to specify the credential within the s url itself important the two method above are mutually exclusive if you pas an aws client and the url contains credential smart open will ignore the latter important smart open ignores configuration file from the older boto library port your old boto setting to boto in order to use them with smart open since going over all or select key in an s bucket is a very common operation there s also an extra function smart open s iter bucket that doe this efficiently processing the bucket key in parallel using multiprocessing smart open us the google cloud storage library to talk to gc google cloud storage us the google cloud package under the hood to handle authentication there are several option to provide credential by default smart open will defer to google cloud storage and let it take care of the credential to override this behavior pas a google cloud storage client object a a transport parameter to the open function you can customize the credential when constructing the client smart open will then use the client when talking to gc to follow allow with the example below refer to google s guide to setting up gc authentication with a service account if you need more credential option you can create an explicit google auth credential credential object and pas it to the client to create an api token for use in the example below refer to the gc authentication guide smart open us the azure storage blob library to talk to azure blob storage by default smart open will defer to azure storage blob and let it take care of the credential azure blob storage doe not have any way of inferring credential therefore passing a azure storage blob blobserviceclient object a a transport parameter to the open function is required you can customize the credential when constructing the client smart open will then use the client when talking to to follow allow with the example below refer to azure s guide to setting up authentication if you need more credential option refer to the azure storage authentication guide smart open open can also be used with path object the built in path open is not able to read text from compressed file so use patch pathlib to replace it with smart open open instead this can be helpful when e g working with compressed file see this document see this document smart open come with a comprehensive suite of unit test before you can run the test suite install the test dependency now you can run the unit test the test are also run automatically with travis ci on every commit push pull request smart open life on github you can file issue or pull request there suggestion pull request and improvement welcome smart open is open source software released under the mit license copyright c now radim eh ek

description: read latest documentation browse github code repositorypreconvert is a library that extends existing serializiers json simplejson bson msgpack to be capable of converting all the type you use it accomplishes this by efficiently preconverting just the type the serializers aren t aware of thing like dataclasses and namedtuples into basic built in type that all serializers can understand it then provides a mechanism for you to build custom preconverters and preconvert plugins that automatically take effect when installed via pip install preconvert using pip replace existing json or other serialization library with preconvert equivalent define preconverters for any custom type even if they aren t under your control enjoy a more comprehensive and configurable serializer have you ever tried to json dump a data structure only to be surprised when your dataclass throw an exception or your namedtuple output a a list preconvert wa created to solve this problem across common serialization format before preconvert after preconvert if your project us one of our built in supported serializers json msgpak bson you can simply replace your existing serializer import with a preconvert one from preconvert output import jsonorfrom preconvert output import simplejson a jsonorfrom preconvert output import msgpackorfrom preconvert output import bsonif not you can inject preconvert before usage of any other serializers often by setting a default or on onknown parameter want to add preconversion to your own custom type for oop project one easy way to do this is to add a preconvert method to your object for other entity such a object you do not control you can register a new preconvert using the preconvert converter decorator you can also optionally specify preconversions per an intended serialization format finally you can resister any module that contain converter to package preconvert converter entrypoints and they will take effect automatically a long a the package that contains them is installed see the preconvert numpy for an example of how this work

description: version v a of see changelog there are many timeout decorator out there that one focus on correctness when using with class method class method static method and so on preserving also the traceback information for pycharm debugging there is also a powerful eval function it allows to read the desired timeout value even from class attribute it is very flexible and can be used with python pypy and probably other dialect there are two timeout strategy implemented the ubiquitous method using signal and the second using multiprocessing using signal is slick and lean but there are nasty caveat please check section caveat using signalsthe default strategy is therefore using multiprocessing but you can also use signal you have been warned due to the lack of signal on window or for threaded function in a subthread where signal cant be used your only choice is multiprocessing this is set automatically under window the decorated function and result need to be pickable for that purpose we use multiprocess and dill instead of multiprocessing and pickle in order to be able to use this decorator on more sophisticated object communication to the subprocess is done via multiprocess pipe instead of queue which is faster and might also work on amazon aws automated test travis matrix documentation badge etc are managed with pizzacutter cookiecutter on steroid python version required or newertested on recent linux with python pypy architecture amd code coverage flake style checking mypy static type checking tested under linux macos window automatic daily build and monitoringtry it onlineusageusage from commandlineinstallation and upgraderequirementsacknowledgementscontributereport issuespull requestcode of conductlicensechangelogyou might try it right away in jupyter notebook by using the launch binder badge or click heredont sprincle your code with timeouts just use it were absolutely necessary for instance when reading or writing a file and do that on the lowest abstraction level possible to avoid unwanted side effect exception caught by some other code non pickable function or argument and so on but not too low remember that forking the program take some time when use multiprocessing most function and library you call they have already some timeouts use those this timeout decorator should be only the last ressort if everything else fails bad example pseudocode let assume the write to the database fails sometimes for unknown reason and hang better example pseudocode for the impatient all you need to do is to put the decorated function into another module not in the main program for those who want to dive deeper on window the main module is imported again but with a name main because python is trying to simulate a forking like behavior on a system that doesn t support forking multiprocessing try to create an environment similar to your main process by importing the main module again with a different name thats why you need to shield the entry point of your program with the famous if name main this is a problem of window o because the window operating system doe not support fork you can find more information on that here http stackoverflow com question workaround for using name main in python multiprocessinghttps doc python org library multiprocessing html windowssince main py is loaded again with a different name but main the decorated function now point to object that do not exist anymore therefore you need to put the decorated class and function into another module in general especially on window the main program should not have anything but the main function the real thing should happen in the module i am also used to put all setting or configuration in a different file so all process or thread can access them and also to keep them in one place together not to forget typing hint and name completion in your favorite editor the dill serializer is able to serialize also the main context that mean the object in our example are pickled to main lib foo main some module main main etc we would not have this limitation when using pickle with the downside that pickle can not serialize following type function with yield nested function lambda cell method unboundmethod module code methodwrapper dictproxy methoddescriptor getsetdescriptor memberdescriptor wrapperdescriptor xrange slice notimplemented ellipsis quitadditional dill support save and load python interpreter session save and extract the source code from function and class interactively diagnose pickling errorsto support more type with the decorator we selected dill a serializer with the small downside that method and class can not be decorated in the main context but need to reside in a module you can find more information on that here http stackoverflow com question serializing an object in main with pickle or dilltiming since spawning take some unknown timespan all import need to be done again you can specify when the timeout should start please read the section hard timeouthere an example that will work on linux but wont work on window the variable name and the function sleep wont be found in the spawned process here the same example which will work on window a abadger point out in his blog using signal and the timeoutexception is probably not the best idea because it can be catched in the decorated function of course you can use your own exception derived from the base exception class but the code might still not work a expected see the next example you may try it out in jupyter by default we use multiprocessing to archive the timeout function basically this is done like that on window hat might take a long timethe main context need to be guarded see section usage with window on window the function code itself and all argument need to be pickable we use dill to offer more type here function parameter and function result need to be pickablebear in mind that if code run in a child process try to access a global variable then the value it see if any may not be the same a the value in the parent process at the time that process wa called however global variable which are just module level constant cause no problem the forked function is run in a subprocessparameters and result are passed via pipe pickled we use dill here the subprocess need to be able to terminate so you must not disable the sigterm handlersince there is only one alarm signal on unix per process you need to use use signal false for nested timeouts the outmost decorator might use signal all nested decorator need to use use signal false the default you may try it out in jupyter specify an alternate exception to raise on timeout decorator parameter starting with dec and use signal can be overridden by kwargs with the same name by default timeout decorator us signal to limit the execution time of the given function this approach doe not work if your function is executed not in the main thread for example if it s a worker thread of the web application or when the operating system doe not support signal aka window there is an alternative timeout strategy for this case by using multiprocessing this is done automatically so you dont need to set use signal false you can force not to use signal on linux by passing the parameter use signal false to the timeout decorator function for testing if your program should also run on window i recommend to test under window since window doe not support forking read more under section use with window the following code will run on linux but not on window warningmake sure that in case of multiprocessing strategy for timeout your function doe not return object which cannot be pickled otherwise it will fail at marshalling it between master and child process to cover more case we use multiprocess and dill instead of multiprocessing and pickle since signal will not work on window it is disabled by default whatever you set you can use the timout also a function without using a decorator this is very powerful but can be also very dangerous if you accept string to evaluate from untrusted input read http nedbatchelder com blog eval really is dangerous htmlif enabled the parameter of the function dec timeout or the parameter passed by kwarg dec timeout will be evaluated if it type is string you can access the decorated function and it attribute example instance x an attribute of the instance of the class instanceexample args the timeout is the first argument in argsexample kwargs max time by default allow eval is disabled but you can enable it in order to cover some edge case without modifying the timeout decorator remember that decorated function and their result need to be pickable under window in order to detect pickle problem you can use when signal false on window logging in the wrapped function can be tricky since a new process is created we can not use the logger object of the main process further development is needed to connect to the main process logger via a socket or queue when the wrapped function is using logger logging getlogger a new logger object is created setting up that logger can be tricky file logging from two process is not supported i think i will use a socket to implement that sockethandler and some receiver thread until then you need to set up your own new logger in the decorated function if logging is needed again keep in mind that you can not write to the same logfile from different process although there are logging module which can do that when use signal false this is the only method available on window the timeout function is realized by starting another process and terminate that process after the given timeout under linux fork of a new process is very fast under window it might take some considerable time because the main context need to be reloaded on spawn spawning of a small module might take something like second and more by default when using signal false the timeout begin after the new process is created this mean that the timeout given is the time the decorated process is allowed to run not included the time excluding the time to setup the process itself this is especially important if you use small timeout period for instance the total time to timeout on linux with use signal false will be around second but on window this can take about second second to spawn the new process and giving the function test second to run if you need that a decorated function should timeout exactly after the given timeout period you can pas the parameter dec hard timeout true in this case the called function will timeout exactly after the given time no matter how long it took to spawn the process itself in that case if you set up the timeout too short the process might never run and will always timeout during spawning well more or le exactly it still take some short time to return from the spawned process so be extra cautious on very short timeouts for local mypy testing please make sure that the stub file wrapt pyi is in in the mypy path once in order to preserve the decorated function signature before you start it highly recommended to update pip and setup tool to install the latest release from pypi via pip recommended to install the latest version from github via pip include it into your requirement txt to install the latest development version from source code via makefile makefiles are a very convenient way to install here we can do much more like installing virtual environment clean cache and so on following module will be automatically installed special thanks to uncle bob robert c martin especially for his book on clean code and clean architecture i would love for you to fork and send me pull request decorating class method fails with dill upwardsupdate test to the latest python version add test for thread lock preserve signature of the decorator remedy mypy untyped decorator make function cli description: this mini package let you get information about what a frame is currently doing particularly the ast node being executed then node will be an ast node from the ast standard library module or none if the node couldn t be identified which may happen often and should always be checked node will always be the same instance for multiple call with frame at the same point of execution if you have a traceback object pas it directly to source executing rather than the tb frame attribute to get the correct node for this you will need to separately install the asttokens library then obtain an asttokens object or or use one of the convenience method or everything go through the source class only one instance of the class is created for each filename subclassing it to add more attribute on creation or method is recommended the classmethods such a executing will respect this see the source code and docstrings for more detail if you don t like that you can just copy the file executing py there are no dependency but of course you won t get update suppose the frame is executing this line and in particular it s currently obtaining the attribute self foo looking at the bytecode specifically frame f code co code frame f lasti we can tell that it s loading an attribute but it s not obvious which one we can narrow down the statement being executed using frame f lineno and find the two ast attribute node representing self foo and bar x how do we find out which one it is without recreating the entire compiler in python the trick is to modify the ast slightly for each candidate expression and observe the change in the bytecode instruction we change the ast to this and compile it and the bytecode will be almost the same but there will be two new instruction and just before that will be a load attr instruction corresponding to self foo seeing that it s in the same position a the original instruction let u know we ve found our match yes if it identifies a node you can trust that it s identified the correct one the test are very thorough in addition to unit test which check various situation directly there are property test against a large number of file see the filename printed in this build with real code specifically for each file the test in other word it show that there is a one to one mapping between the node and the instruction that can be handled this leaf very little room for a bug to creep in furthermore executing check that the instruction compiled from the modified ast exactly match the original code save for a few small known exception this account for all the quirk and optimisation in the interpreter currently it work in almost all case for the following ast node the plan is to extend to more operation in the future

description: shellingham detects what shell the current python executable is running in detect shell poke around the process s running environment to determine what shell it is run in it return a tuple the shell name always lowercased the command used to run the shell shelldetectionfailure is raised if detect shell fails to detect the surrounding shell the shell name is always lowercased on window the shell name is the name of the executable minus the file extension remember your application s user is not necessarily using a shell shellingham raise shelldetectionfailure if there is no shell to detect but your application should almost never do this to your user a practical approach to this is to wrap detect shell in a try block and provide a sane default on failure there are a few choice for you to choose from the posix standard mandate the environment variable shell to refer to the user s preferred command language interpreter this is always available even if the user is not in an interactive session and likely the correct choice to launch an interactive sub shell with a command sh is almost guaranteed to exist likely at bin sh since several posix tool rely on it this should be suitable if you want to run a possibly non interactive script all version of do and window have an environment variable comspec this can always be used to launch a usable command prompt e g cmd exe on window here s a simple implementation to provide a default shell
