description: this python module allows you to merge a series of json document into a single one this problem often occurs for example when different author fill in different part of a common document and you need to construct a document that includes contribution from all the author it also help when dealing with consecutive version of a document where different field get updated over time consider a trivial example with two document we call the document we are merging change into base and the changed document head to merge these two document using jsonmerge a you can see when encountering an json object jsonmerge by default return field that appear in either base or head document for other json type it simply replaces the older value these principle are also applied in case of multiple nested json object in a more realistic use case however you might want to apply different merge strategy to different part of the document you can tell jsonmerge how to do that using a syntax based on json schema if you already have schema for your document you can simply expand them with some additional keywords apart from the custom keywords described below jsonmerge by default us the schema syntax defined in the draft of the json schema specification you use the mergestrategy schema keyword to specify the strategy the default two strategy mentioned above are called objectmerge for object and overwrite for all other type let s say you want to specify that the merged bar field in the example document above should contain element from all document not just the latest one you can do this with a schema like this another common example is when you need to keep a versioned list of value that appeared in the series of document note that we use the mergeoptions keyword in the schema to supply additional option to the merge strategy in this case we tell the version strategy to retain only most recent version of this field we also used the merge option argument to supply some option that are specific to each call of the merge method option specified this way are applied to all invocation of a specific strategy in a schema in contrast to mergeoptions which applies only to the strategy invocation in that specific location in the schema option specified in mergeoptions schema keyword override the option specified in the merge option argument the metadata option for the version strategy can contain some document meta data that is included for each version of the field metadata can contain an arbitrary json object example above also demonstrates how jsonmerge is typically used when merging more than two document typically you start with an empty base and then consecutively merge different head into it a common source of problem are document that do not match the schema used for merging jsonmerge by itself doe not validate input document it only us the schema to obtain necessary information to apply appropriate merge strategy since the default strategy are used for part of the document that are not covered by the schema it s easy to get unexpected output without any obvious error raised by jsonmerge in the following example the property foo uppercase f doe not match foo lowercase f in the schema and hence the version strategy is not applied a with previous two revision hence it is recommended to validate the input document against the schema before passing them to jsonmerge this practice is even more effective if the schema is filled in with more information than strictly necessary for jsonmerge e g adding information about type restrict valid object property with additionalproperties etc if you care about well formedness of your document you might also want to obtain a schema for the document that the merge method creates jsonmerge provides a way to automatically generate it from a schema for the input document note that because of the version strategy the type of the foo field changed from object to array these are the currently implemented merge strategy overwrite with the value in base with value in head work with any type keep the value in base even if head contains a different value work with any type by default if base doe not contain any value i e that part of the document is undefined the value after merge is kept undefined this can be changed with the keepifundef option if this option is true then the value from head will be retained in this case this is useful if you are merging a series of document and want to keep the value that first appears in the series but want to discard further modification append array work only with array you can specify a sortbyref merge option to indicate the key that will be used to sort the item in the array this option can be an arbitrary json pointer when resolving the pointer the root is placed at the root of the array item sort order can be reversed by setting the sortreverse option merge array identifying item to be merged by an id field resulting array have item from both base and head array any item that have identical an id are merged based on the strategy specified further down in the hierarchy by default array item are expected to be object and id of the item is obtained from the id property of the object you can specify an arbitrary json pointer to point to the id of the item using the idref merge option when resolving the pointer document root is placed at the root of the array item e g by default idref is id you can also set idref to to treat an array of integer or string a a set of unique value array item in head for which the id cannot be identified e g idref pointer is invalid are ignored you can specify an additional item id to be ignored using the ignoreid merge option a compound id can be specified by setting idref to an array of pointer in that case if any pointer in the array is invalid for an object in head the object is ignored if using an array for idref and if ignoreid option is also defined ignoreid must be an array a well you can specify a sortbyref merge option to indicate the key that will be used to sort the item in the array this option can be an arbitrary json pointer the pointer is resolved in the same way a idref sort order can be reversed by setting the sortreverse option merge array item by their index in the array similarly to arraymergebyid strategy the resulting array have item from both base and head array item that occur at identical position in both array will be merged based on the strategy specified further down in the hierarchy merge object resulting object have property from both base and head any property that are present both in base and head are merged based on the strategy specified further down in the hierarchy e g in property patternproperties or additionalproperties schema keywords the objclass option allows one to request a different dictionary class to be used to hold the json object the possible value are name that correspond to specific python class built in name include ordereddict to use the collection ordereddict class or dict which us the python s dict built in if not specified dict is used by default note that additional class or a different default can be configured via the merger constructor see below change the type of the value to an array new value are appended to the array in the form of an object with a value property this way all value seen during the merge are preserved you can add additional property to the appended object using the metadata option additionally you can use metadataschema option to specify the schema for the object in the metadata option you can limit the length of the list using the limit option in the mergeoptions keyword by default if a head document contains the same value a the base document no new version will be appended you can change this by setting ignoredups option to false if a merge strategy is not specified in the schema objectmerge is used for object and overwrite for all other value but see also the section below regarding keywords that apply subschemas you can implement your own strategy by making subclass of jsonmerge strategy strategy and passing them to merger constructor see below the merger class allows you to further customize the merging of json data by allowing you to set the schema containing the merge strategy configuration provide additional strategy implementation set a default class to use for holding json object data andconfigure additional json object class selectable via the objclass merge option the merger constructor take the following argument all optional except schema the json schema that contains the merge strategy directive provided a a json object an empty dictionary should be provided if no strategy configuration is needed a dictionary mapping strategy name to instance of strategy class these will be combined with the built in strategy overriding them with the instance having the same name the name of a supported dictionary like class to hold json data by default in the merged result the name must match a built in name or one provided in the objclass menu parameter a dictionary providing additional class to use a json object container the key are name that can be used a value for the objectmerge strategy s objclass option or the objclass def argument each value is a function or class that produce an instance of the json object container it must support an optional dictionary like object a a parameter which initializes it content a jsonschema validator subclass this can be used to specify which json schema draft version will be used during merge some detail such a reference resolution are different between version by default the draft validator is used complex merging of document with schema that use keywords allof anyof and oneof can be problematic such document do not have a well defined type and might require merging of two value of different type which will fail for some strategy in such case get schema might also return schema that never validate the overwrite strategy is usually the safest choice for such schema if you explicitly define a merge strategy at the same level a allof anyof or oneof keyword then jsonmerge will use the defined strategy and not further process any subschemas under those keywords the strategy however will descend a usual e g objectmerge will take into account subschemas under the property keyword at the same level a allof if a merge strategy is not explicitly defined and an allof or anyof keyword is present jsonmerge will raise an error if a merge strategy is not explicitly defined and an oneof keyword is present jsonmerge will continue on the branch of oneof that validates both base and head if no branch validates it will raise an error you can define more complex behavior by defining for your own strategy that defines what to do in such case see docstring documentation for the strategy class on how to do that a json schema document can contain ref reference to external schema jsonmerge resolve uris in these reference using the mechanism provided by the jsonschema module external reference can cause http or similar network request to be performed if jsonmerge is used on untrusted input this may lead to vulnerability similar to the xml external entity xxe attack jsonmerge support python and python and newer you need jsonschema http pypi python org pypi jsonschema module installed to install the latest jsonmerge release from the python package index the latest development version is available on github http github com avian jsonmergeto install from source run the following from the top of the source distribution jsonmerge us tox for testing to run the test suite run thank you for contributing to jsonmerge free software wouldn t be possible without contribution from user like you however please consider that i maintain this project in my free time hence i ask you to follow this simple etiquette to minimize the amount of effort needed to include your contribution please use github issue to report bug make sure that your report includes a minimal but complete code example that reproduces the problem including any json data required to run it it should be something i can copy paste into a py file and run relevant version of jsonmerge either release number on pypi or git commit hash copy of the traceback in case you are reporting an unhandled exception example of what you think should be the correct output in case you are reporting wrong result of a merge or schema generation please use github pull request to contribute code make sure that your pull request pass all existing test and includes new test that cover added code update readme rst to document added description: this repository contains the pytorch implementation of open unmix a deep neural network reference implementation for music source separation applicable for researcher audio engineer and artist open unmix provides ready to use model that allow user to separate pop music into four stem vocal drum bass and the remaining other instrument the model were pre trained on the freely available musdb dataset see detail at apply pre trained model we added umxl a model that wa trained on extra data which significantly improves the performance especially generalization we released the new version of open unmix a a python package this come with a fully differentiable version of norbert improved audio loading pipeline and large number of bug fix see release note for further info we added a pre trained speech enhancement model umxse provided by sony open unmix wa awarded nd place in the pytorch global summer hackathon related project open unmix pytorch open unmix nnabla musdb museval norbertto perform separation into multiple source open unmix comprises multiple model that are trained for each particular target while this make the training le comfortable it allows great flexibility to customize the training data for each target source each open unmix source model is based on a three layer bidirectional deep lstm the model learns to predict the magnitude spectrogram of a target source like vocal from the magnitude spectrogram of a mixture input internally the prediction is obtained by applying a mask on the input the model is optimized in the magnitude domain using mean squared error open unmix operates in the time frequency domain to perform it prediction the input of the model is either model separator a time domain signal tensor of shape nb sample nb channel nb timesteps where nb sample are the sample in a batch nb channel is or for mono or stereo audio respectively and nb timesteps is the number of audio sample in the recording in this case the model computes stfts with either torch or asteroid filteranks on the fly model openunmix the core open unmix take magnitude spectrogram directly e g when pre computed and loaded from disk in that case the input is of shape nb frame nb sample nb channel nb bin where nb frame and nb bin are the time and frequency dimension of a short time fourier transform the input spectrogram is standardized using the global mean and standard deviation for every frequency bin across all frame furthermore we apply batch normalization in multiple stage of the model to make the training more robust against gain variation the lstm is not operating on the original input spectrogram resolution instead in the first step after the normalization the network learns to compress the frequency and channel axis of the model to reduce redundancy and make the model converge faster the core of open unmix is a three layer bidirectional lstm network due to it recurrent nature the model can be trained and evaluated on arbitrary length of audio signal since the model take information from past and future simultaneously the model cannot be used in an online real time manner an uni directional model can easily be trained a described here after applying the lstm the signal is decoded back to it original input dimensionality in the last step the output is multiplied with the input magnitude spectrogram so that the model is asked to learn a mask model separator put together open unmix spectrogram model for each desired target and combine their output through a multichannel generalized wiener filter before application of inverse stfts using torchaudio the filtering is differentiable but parameter free version of norbert the separator is currently currently only used during inference openunmix can be installed from pypi using note that the pypi version of openunmix us torchaudio to load and save audio file to increase the number of supported input and output file format such a stem export please additionally install stempeg training is not part of the open unmix package please follow doc train md for more information we also provide a docker container performing separation of a local track in music track wav can be performed in a single line we provide three core pre trained music separation model all three model are end to end model that take waveform input and output the separated waveform umxl default trained on private stem dataset of compressed stem note that the weight are only licensed for non commercial use cc by nc sa umxhq trained on musdb hq which comprises the same track a in musdb but un compressed which yield in a full bandwidth of hz umx is trained on the regular musdb which is bandwidth limited to khz do to aac compression this model should be used for comparison with other older method for evaluation in sisec furthermore we provide a model for speech enhancement trained by sony corporationumxse speech enhancement model is trained on the speaker version of the voicebank demand corpus all four model are also available a spectrogram core model which take magnitude spectrogram input and ouput separated spectrogram these model can be loaded using umxl spec umxhq spec umx spec and umxse spec to separate audio file wav flac ogg but not mp file just run a more detailed list of the parameter used for the separation is given in the inference md document we provide a jupyter notebook on google colab to experiment with open unmix and to separate file online without any installation setup we implementes several way to load pre trained model and use them from within your python project loading a pre trained model is a simple a loadingwe also provide a torch hub compatible module that can be loaded note that this doe not even require to install the open unmix packagen and should generally work when the pytorch version is the same where umxl specifies the pre trained model with a created separator object one can perform separation of some audio torch tensor of shape channel length provided a at a sampling rate separator sample rate through note that this requires the audio to be in the right shape and sampling rate for convenience we provide a pre processing in openunmix utils preprocess that take numpy audio and convert it to be used for open unmix to perform model loading preprocessing and separation in one step just use when a path instead of a model name is provided to model pre trained separator will be loaded from disk e g the following file are assumed to present when loading model mymodel target vocalsnote that the separator usually join multiple model for each target and performs separation using all model e g if the separator contains vocal and drum model two output file are generated unless the residual option is selected in which case an additional source will be produced containing an estimate of all that is not the target in the mixture to perform evaluation in comparison to other sisec system you would need to install the museval package usingand then run the evaluation usingpython m openunmix evaluate outdir path to musdb estimate evaldir path to museval resultsopen unmix yield state of the art result compared to participant from sisec the performance of umxhq and umx is almost identical since it wa evaluated on compressed stem note thatdetails on the training is provided in a separate document here detail on how open unmix can be extended or improved for future research on music separation is described in a separate document here we favored simplicity over performance to promote clearness of the code the rationale is to have open unmix serve a a baseline for future research while performance still meet current state of the art see evaluation the result are comparable better to those of uhl uhl which obtained the best performance over all system trained on musdb in the sisec evaluation campaign we designed the code to allow researcher to reproduce existing result quickly develop new architecture and add own user data for training and testing we favored framework specific implementation instead of having a monolithic repository with common code for all framework open unmix is a community focused project we therefore encourage the community to submit bug fix and request for technical support through github issue for more detail of how to contribute please follow our contributing md for help and support please use the gitter chat or the google group forum fabian robert st ter antoine liutkus inria and lirmm montpellier france misc musdb author rafii zafar and description: dart is a python library for easy manipulation and forecasting of time series it contains a variety of model from classic such a arima to deep neural network the model can all be used in the same way using fit and predict function similar to scikit learn the library also make it easy to backtest model combine the prediction of several model and take external data into account dart support both univariate and multivariate time series and model the ml based model can be trained on potentially large datasets containing multiple time series and some of the model offer a rich support for probabilistic forecasting we recommend to first setup a clean python environment for your project with python using your favorite tool conda venv virtualenv with or without virtualenvwrapper once your environment is set up you can install dart using pip for more detail you can refer to our installation instruction create a timeseries object from a panda dataframe and split it in train validation series fit an exponential smoothing model and make a probabilistic prediction over the validation series duration plot the median th and th percentile here s a breakdown of the forecasting model currently implemented in dart we are constantly working on bringing more model and feature anyone is welcome to join our discord server gitter room to ask question make proposal discus use case and more if you spot a bug or or have suggestion github issue are also welcome if what you want to tell u is not suitable for discord or github feel free to send u an email at dart unit co for dart related matter or info unit co for any other inquiry the development is ongoing and we welcome suggestion pull request and issue on github all contributor will be acknowledged on the change log page before working on a contribution a new feature or a fix check our contribution guideline if you are using dart in your scientific work we would appreciate citation to the following jmlr paper dart user friendly modern machine learning for time seriesbibtex entry

description: http github com omni u jsonargparse this package is an extension to python s argparse which simplifies parsing of configuration option from command line argument json configuration file yaml or jsonnet supersets environment variable and hard coded default the aim is similar to other project such a configargparse yconf confuse typer omegaconf fire and click the obvious question is why yet another package similar to many already existing one the answer is simply that none of the existing project had the exact feature we wanted and after analyzing the alternative it seemed simpler to start a new project great support of type hint for automatic creation of parser and minimal boilerplate command line interface non intrusive decoupled parsing logic no need to inherit from a special class or add decorator or use custom type hint easy to implement configurable dependency injection object composition support for nested namespaces making possible to parse config file with non flat hierarchy parsing of relative path within config file and path list support for two popular supersets of json yaml and jsonnet parser can be configured just like with python s argparse thus it ha a gentle learning curve several convenient type and action class to ease common parsing use case path comparison operator json schema enums regex string support for command line tab argument completion using argcomplete configuration value are overridden based on the following precedence parsing command line command line argument might include config file environment variable default config file default parsing file config file environment variable default config file default parsing environment environment variable default config file default you can install using pip a by default the only dependency that jsonargparse installs is pyyaml however several optional feature can be enabled by specifying any of the following extra requires signature jsonschema jsonnet url argcomplete and reconplogger there is also the all extra require to enable all optional feature installing jsonargparse with extra require is a follows the following table reference section that describe optional feature and the corresponding extra requires that enables them url fsspecargcompletejsonnetjsonschemasignaturesclasses method function parsing url json schema jsonnet file tab completion there are multiple way of using jsonargparse one is to construct low level parser see parser being almost a drop in replacement of argparse however argparse is too verbose and lead to unnecessary duplication the simplest and recommended way of using jsonargparse is by using the cli function which ha the benefit of minimizing boilerplate code a simple example is note that the name and prize parameter have type hint and are described in the docstring these are shown in the help of the command line tool in a shell you could see the help and run a command a follows cli without argument search for function and class defined in the same module and in the local context where cli is called giving a single or a list of function class a first argument to cli skip the automatic search and only includes what is given when cli receives a single class the first argument are for parameter to instantiate the class then a method name is expected i e method become sub command and the remaining argument are for parameter of this method an example would be then in a shell you could run if more than one function is given to cli then any of them can be run via sub command similar to the single class example above i e example py function argument where function is the name of the function to execute if multiple class or a mixture of function and class is given to cli to execute a method of a class two level of sub command are required the first sub command would be the name of the class and the second the name of the method i e example py class init argument method argument notethe two example above are extremely simple only defining parameter with str and int type hint the true power of jsonargparse is it support for a wide range of type see type hint it is even possible to use general class a type hint allowing to easily implement configurable dependency injection object composition see sub class all tool implemented with the cli function have the config option to provide setting in a config file more detail in configuration file this becomes very useful when the number of configurable parameter is large to ease the writing of config file there is also the option print config automatically printed cli return the value and it is up to the developer to decide what to do with it jsonargparse say goodbye to configuration hassle by marianne stecklina at pycon de pydata berlin
